                  <h1 class=3D"title topictitle1" id=3D"ariaid-title1">Lice=
nsing the
                     	 Firepower System
                  </h1>
                  <section class=3D"body">
                     <p class=3D"p">The
                        Licensing chapter of the Firepower Management Cente=
r Configuration Guide provides in-depth information about the
                        different license types, service subscriptions, lic=
ensing requirements and more. The
                        chapter also provides procedures and requirements f=
or deploying Smart and Classic
                        licenses and licensing for air-gapped solutions.
                     </p>
                     <p class=3D"p">The following topics explain how to lic=
ense Firepower. </p>
                  </section>
                  <!-- minitoc start -->

                  <article class=3D"topic concept nested1" aria-labelledby=
=3D"ariaid-title2" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"ID-2240-00000006">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title2">A=
bout Firepower Licenses</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                        <p class=3D"p">Your Firepower products (<span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> and ma=
naged devices) include licenses for basic operation, but some features requ=
ire separate licensing or service subscriptions,
                           as described in this chapter.=20
                        </p>
                        <p class=3D"p">A "right-to-use" license does not ex=
pire, but service subscriptions require periodic renewal. </p>
                        <p class=3D"p">The type of license your products re=
quire <span class=3D"ph">(Smart or Classic) </span>depends on the software =
you use, not on the hardware it runs on.
                        </p>
                       =20
                        <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"olh_n=
ote" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                           <tbody><tr>
                              <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=3D"h=
eading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/us/td=
/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                              </td>
                              <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                 <section class=3D"note__content">
                                    <hr>
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">"NGFW" means different t=
hings to different people, so this documentation does not use this term.</p=
>
                                   =20
                                    <hr>
                                 </section>
                              </td>
                           </tr>
                        </tbody></table></div>
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></nav=
>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic reference nested1" aria-labelledb=
y=3D"ariaid-title3" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"Cisco_Reference.dita_fc0a2f25-04aa=
-4097-8b6e-5593a1cf7dd5">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title3">R=
equirements and Prerequisites for Licensing</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body refbody">
                       =20
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"Cisco_Reference.di=
ta_fc0a2f25-04aa-4097-8b6e-5593a1cf7dd5__d262094e173">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle"><span class=3D"=
ph">Model Support</span></h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Any, but the specific licenses re=
quires per model differ as indicated in the
                              procedures.
                           </p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                       =20
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"Cisco_Reference.di=
ta_fc0a2f25-04aa-4097-8b6e-5593a1cf7dd5__d262094e183">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle"><span class=3D"=
ph">Supported Domains</span></h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph">Global</span>,=
 except where indicated.
                           </p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                       =20
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"Cisco_Reference.di=
ta_fc0a2f25-04aa-4097-8b6e-5593a1cf7dd5__d262094e195">

ph">User Roles</span></h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <ul class=3D"ul">
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph">Admin</s=
pan></p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20

                        </section>

                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic concept nested1" aria-labelledby=
=3D"ariaid-title4" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_87679">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title4">L=
icense Requirements for Firepower Management Center</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                        <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_87679__ID-2240-0000001a"><s=
pan class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></spa=
n> allows you to assign licenses to managed devices and manage licenses for=
 the system.=20
                        </p>
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_87679__d262094e=
244">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Hardware FMC</h=
3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">A hardware <span class=3D"ph"><sp=
an class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> does not require =
purchase of additional licenses or service subscriptions in order to manage=
 devices.
                           </p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_87679__d262094e=
256">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Virtual FMC</h3=
>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D=
"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> Virtual has additional licen=
sing requirements.=20
                              <span class=3D"ph">See <a class=3D"xref" href=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configurati=
on/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#referenc=
e_32D26DAA9C3445008CD8E72E598191E3">Firepower Management Center Virtual Lic=
enses</a>.</span></p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links">
                        <ul class=3D"ullinks">
                           <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https:=
//www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/f=
pmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#reference_32D26DAA=
9C3445008CD8E72E598191E3">Firepower Management Center Virtual Licenses</a><=
/li>
                        </ul>
                     </nav>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                     <article class=3D"topic reference nested2" aria-labell=
edby=3D"ariaid-title5" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"reference_32D26DAA9C3445008CD8E=
72E598191E3">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title5=
">Firepower Management
                           	 Center Virtual Licenses
                        </h3>
                        <section class=3D"body refbody">
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_32D26=
DAA9C3445008CD8E72E598191E3__section_97615F61BF504949A0A82D0D6827FD0C">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Generally, <span class=3D"ph">=
<span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> Virtual (FMCv)=
 requires a license entitlement
                                 for each FTD device that it will manage.=
=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">FMCv does not require Smart li=
censes
                                 (Firepower MCv) to manage Classic devices.=
 Classic
                                 devices need PAK licenses to be installed =
via
                                 FMCv. However, when you purchase an FMCv25=
, 25 MCv
                                 Entitlements are deposited in your Smart A=
ccount.
                                 If your FMCv manages both Classic (7K/8K/F=
P
                                 Services and Smart FTDs) and your device l=
imit
                                 reaches 25, you see an error in FMC but yo=
ur Smart
                                 License will still comply with the additio=
nal MCv
                                 Entitlements.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">In case of an FTDv high availa=
bility
                                 configuration, you require two MCv license=
s for
                                 every FTDv device.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">If a single FMCv manages Firep=
ower Threat Defense devices that are configured in a high availability pair=
, you still need
                                 one entitlement for each device (<em class=
=3D"ph i">not</em> one entitlement for the pair of FTDs.)
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">For FMCv in high availability =
configurations, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us=
/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/fi=
repower_management_center_high_availability.html#id_21090">License Requirem=
ents for FMC High Availability Configurations</a>.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">In multi-instance deployments,=
 you need one entitlement for each security module.
                                =20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">In standard, connected Smart L=
icensing, these licenses are perpetual. </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">In Specific License Reservatio=
n, these licenses are term-based.</p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">This entitlement appears in Ci=
sco Smart Software Manager as <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Firepower MCv De=
vice License</span> with different numbers of entitlements.
                              </p>=20
                              	=20
                           </section>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic concept nested1" aria-labelledby=
=3D"ariaid-title6" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_93998">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title6">E=
valuation License Caveats</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                        <p class=3D"p">Not all functionality is available w=
ith an evaluation license, functionality under an evaluation license may be=
 partial, and
                           transition from evaluation licensing to standard=
 licensing may not be seamless.=20
                        </p>
                        <p class=3D"p">For example, if you have Firepower T=
hreat Defense devices configured in a cluster, and you switch from an evalu=
ation license
                           to Smart Licensing, service will be interrupted =
when you deploy the change.
                        </p>
                        <p class=3D"p">Review information about evaluation =
license caveats in information about particular features in this Licensing =
chapter and
                           in the chapters related to deploying each featur=
e.
                        </p>
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></nav=
>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic concept nested1" aria-labelledby=
=3D"ariaid-title7" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_75735">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title7">S=
mart vs. Classic Licenses</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                        <p class=3D"p">For managed devices, the licenses yo=
u need (Smart or Classic) depend on the software that runs on the device. <=
/p>
                       =20
                        <p class=3D"p">Any FMC can simultaneously manage de=
vices with Smart and Classic licenses. You must configure each type of lice=
nsing separately.</p>
                        <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table width=3D"100%"=
 border=3D"1" class=3D"table frame-all">
                           <caption></caption>
                           <colgroup>
                              <col style=3D"width:28.57142857142857%">
                              <col style=3D"width:14.285714285714285%">
                              <col style=3D"width:57.14285714285714%">
                           </colgroup>
                           <thead class=3D"thead">
                              <tr>
                                 <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"entry al=
ign-left colsep-1 rowsep-1" id=3D"id_75735__entry__1">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Software</p>
                                   =20
                                 </th>
                                 <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"entry al=
ign-left colsep-1 rowsep-1" id=3D"id_75735__entry__2">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">License Type</p>
                                   =20
                                 </th>
                                 <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"entry al=

                  <article class=3D"topic concept nested1" aria-labelledby=
=3D"ariaid-title8" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"concept_5B8D7BC78F154A34A31118D05B2=
6D851">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title8">L=
icense Firepower Threat Defense Devices (FTD)</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                        <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph=
">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> devices require Smart Licensing.
                        </p>
                        <p class=3D"p">Cisco Smart Licensing
                           		lets you purchase and manage a pool of license=
s centrally. Unlike product
                           		authorization key (PAK) licenses, Smart Licens=
es are not tied to a specific
                           		serial number or license key. Smart Licensing =
lets you assess your license
                           		usage and needs at a glance.=20
                           	=20
                        </p>
                        <p class=3D"p">In addition, Smart
                           		Licensing does not prevent you from using prod=
uct features that you have not
                           		yet purchased. You can start using a license i=
mmediately, as long as you are
                           		registered with the Cisco Smart Software Manag=
er, and purchase the license
                           		later. This allows you to deploy and use a fea=
ture, and avoid delays due to
                           		purchase order approval.=20
                           	=20
                        </p>
                        <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"olh_n=
ote" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                           <tbody><tr>
                              <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=3D"h=
eading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/us/td=
/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                              </td>
                              <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                 <section class=3D"note__content">
                                    <hr>
                                    		=09
                                    <p class=3D"p">At the end of <span clas=
s=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> initial configuration the sys=
tem displays a pop-up that offers you the opportunity to quickly and easily=
 set up Smart Licensing.
                                       Using this dialog is optional; if yo=
ur <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> will be managing=
 <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></spa=
n> devices and you are familiar with Smart Licensing, use this dialog. Othe=
rwise dismiss the dialog and use the information
                                       in this chapter to set up Smart Lice=
nsing.
                                    </p>
                                    	=09
                                    <hr>
                                 </section>
                              </td>
                           </tr>
                        </tbody></table></div>
                     </section>

                     <article class=3D"topic task nested2 no_summary_steps"=
 aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title9" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_75733">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title9=
">How to License <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Def=
ense</span></span> Devices
                        </h3>
                        <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                           <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"id_7573=
3__d262094e724">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> devices require Smart Licens=
ing.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Follow the steps outlined in t=
his overview to license FTD devices managed by a hardware or virtual <span =
class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">If your FMC also manages Class=
ic devices (ASA FirePOWER, NGIPSv), you can follow this procedure for FTD d=
evices, then follow
                                 the instructions under <a class=3D"xref" h=
ref=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configur=
ation/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_49=
477">License Classic Devices (ASA FirePOWER and NGIPSv)</a> for devices tha=
t use Classic licensing.
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h4>
                           </section>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"st=
epTable" border=3D"0">
                              <tbody>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">If you do not al=
ready have a Smart Account, create one.</p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">We recommend you h=
ave a Smart Account before you purchase licenses. To create a new Smart Acc=
ount, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/s=
ecurity/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_th=
e_firepower_system.html#id_81767">Create a Smart Account to Hold Your Licen=
ses</a>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <div class=3D"tableContainer"><ta=
ble class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                             <tbody><tr>
                                                <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"t=
d_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                   <p><b>Note</b></p>&nbsp;
                                                </td>
                                                <td border=3D"0" class=3D"t=
d_faq">
                                                   <section class=3D"note__=
content">Your account representative may have created a Smart Account on yo=
ur behalf. If so, make sure you can access the account in
                                                      the Cisco Smart Softw=
are Manager (CSSM) at <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://software.cisco.com/=
#module/SmartLicensing" target=3D"_blank">https://software.cisco.com/#modul=
e/SmartLicensing</a>.
                                                   </section>
                                                </td>
                                             </tr>
                                          </tbody></table></div>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Understand the <=
em class=3D"ph i"><u class=3D"ph u">platform</u></em> licenses your organiz=
ation needs:
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <ul class=3D"ul">
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p"><span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> physic=
al hardware: =20
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">This applian=
ce comes with the licensing it needs; you do not need to do anything to act=
ivate this.</p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p"><span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> Virtua=
l:=20
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">You need add=
itional licenses. For details, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.ci=
sco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-conf=
ig-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#reference_32D26DAA9C344500=
8CD8E72E598191E3">Firepower Management Center Virtual Licenses</a>.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">(If your FMC=
v will also manage devices that use Classic licenses, those devices will al=
so require these entitlements when
                                                   you configure Classic li=
censing.)=20
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p"><span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> devices:
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">Each device =
automatically includes a license for basic functionality. For details, see =
<a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/fi=
repower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepowe=
r_system.html#reference_A00D8504BBA84A27B07B74014AA7337A">Base Licenses</a>=
.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">You do not n=
eed to do anything to activate a base license, but many features require se=
parate licensing, which is discussed
                                                   below.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                          </ul>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Understand the <=
em class=3D"ph i"><u class=3D"ph u">feature</u></em> licenses (sometimes ca=
lled service subscriptions) that your organization needs.
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xr=
ef" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/con=
figuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#=
reference_59A9CDED24034CE2B12D2E633C5C7D2D">FTD License Types and Restricti=
ons</a> and subtopics.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Determine the <e=
m class=3D"ph i"><u class=3D"ph u">number</u></em> of feature licenses/serv=
ice subscriptions that your organization needs.=20
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <ul class=3D"ul">
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">Generally, e=
ach managed device needs to be licensed for each feature you will use.</p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">For <span cl=
ass=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s in=
 a high availability pair:
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">See FMC HA <=
a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/fir=
epower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/firepower_management_ce=
nter_high_availability.html#id_21090">License Requirements for FMC High Ava=
ilability Configurations</a>.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">For <span cl=
ass=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> device=
s in a high availability pair:
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">Each device =
(whether active or standby) must be licensed for each feature to be used. N=
o additional licensing is required.</p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">See <a class=
=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/=
70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/high_availability_for_firepowe=
r_threat_defense.html#id_21494">License Requirements for FTD Devices in a H=
igh Availability Pair</a>.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">For inter- o=
r intra-chassis clustered <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower T=
hreat Defense</span></span> devices:
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">See <a class=
=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/=
70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/clustering_for_the_firepower_t=
hreat_defense.html#id_93999">Licenses for Clustering</a>.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">For a multi-=
instance deployment: </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">See <a class=
=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/=
70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system=
.html#id_82182">Licensing for Multi-Instance Deployments</a>.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                          </ul>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;5</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">If you have exis=
ting licenses that you need to move: </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <ul class=3D"ul">
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">To convert a=
 Classic license to a license that can be used for <span class=3D"ph"><span=
 class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span>:=20
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">See <a class=
=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/=
70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system=
.html#id_79783">How to Convert a Classic License for Use on an FTD Device</=
a>.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">To transfer =
Smart Licenses that are currently registered to another <span class=3D"ph">=
<span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>:=20
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">See <a class=
=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/=
70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system=
.html#concept_5DB3F9F2A08449F7A38FCF8C06516520">Transfer FTD Licenses to a =
Different Firepower Management Center</a> and <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"htt=
ps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guid=
e/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#task_E9C821FFDC=
2A4958A3A5F536E89EB895">Deregister a Firepower Management Center from the C=
isco Smart Software Manager</a>.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">To move Smar=
t Licenses that are currently registered to another <span class=3D"ph"><spa=
n class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> device:=20
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">See <a class=
=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/=
70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system=
.html#task_2386ECC9E89C4D2B940881F1D39ECA45">Move or Remove Licenses from F=
TD Devices</a>.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                          </ul>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;6</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">If your Firepowe=
r appliances have restricted internet access: </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Determine which so=
lution is best for your situation:</p>
                                         =20
                                          <ul class=3D"ul">
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">If your <spa=
n class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>=
 is not connected to the internet, but it can connect to an internal server=
 that can connect to Cisco's licensing authority,
                                                   or can receive manual li=
cense updates:
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">Deploy <span=
 class=3D"ph">Smart Software Manager
                                                      										On-Prem</sp=
an> (formerly known as a Smart Software Satellite Server.) For information,=
 see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/securi=
ty/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_fir=
epower_system.html#id_79843">Smart Software Manager On-Prem Overview</a> an=
d <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/=
firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepo=
wer_system.html#id_79920">How to Deploy Smart Software Manager On-Prem</a>.=
=20
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">If your depl=
oyment is completely air-gapped and cannot connect to the licensing authori=
ty or to <span class=3D"ph">Smart Software Manager
                                                      										On-Prem</sp=
an> (which connects to the licensing authority), or receive manual license =
updates:
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">See the opti=
ons at <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/secu=
rity/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_f=
irepower_system.html#id_79548">Specific License Reservation (SLR)</a> and s=
kip the rest of this procedure.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">For a compar=
ison, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/s=
ecurity/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_th=
e_firepower_system.html#id_85794">Licensing Options for Air-Gapped Deployme=
nts</a>.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                          </ul>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;7</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">If you have mult=
iple <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</spa=
n></span> appliances and you want to connect to Cisco's licensing authority=
 through a single proxy:
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Deploy <span class=
=3D"ph">Smart Software Manager
                                                										On-Prem</span> (f=
ormerly known as a Smart Software Satellite Server.) For information, see <=
a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/fir=
epower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower=
_system.html#id_79843">Smart Software Manager On-Prem Overview</a>.=20
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;8</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">If you want to e=
nable features that use strong encryption and that are restricted by geogra=
phic region: </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xr=
ef" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/con=
figuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#=
id_81552">Licensing for Export-Controlled Functionality</a>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;9</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Purchase the lic=
enses you need:</p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Contact your Cisco=
 sales representative or authorized reseller. </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;10</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Verify that your=
 reseller or Cisco sales representative has added your licenses to your Sma=
rt Account. </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Look in CSSM: <a c=
lass=3D"xref" href=3D"https://software.cisco.com/#SmartLicensing-Inventory"=
 target=3D"_blank">https://software.cisco.com/#SmartLicensing-Inventory</a>=
. Click <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Inventory</span>, then the <span class=
=3D"ph uicontrol">Licenses</span> tab. Filter the list as needed. You may n=
eed your purchase confirmation in order to understand the license naming.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">If you don't see t=
he licenses you expect to see, make sure you are looking at the correct vir=
tual account. For assistance
                                             with this, see the resource li=
nks in CSSM.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">If you still don't=
 see your licenses, or the licenses are not correct, contact the person fro=
m whom you purchased the licenses.
                                            =20
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;11</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">After your virtu=
al account (Smart Account) holds the licenses you expect, register your <sp=
an class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span=
> to CSSM:
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">You must configure=
 licensing in the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Managemen=
t Center</span></span> using the web interface.=20
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <ul class=3D"ul">
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">If your <spa=
n class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>=
 connects directly to CSSM:
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">See the foll=
owing topics:</p>
                                               =20
                                                <ul class=3D"ul">
                                                   <li class=3D"li">
                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p"><a cla=
ss=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepowe=
r/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_syst=
em.html#id_81330">Obtain a Product License Registration Token for Smart Lic=
ensing</a> and=20
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                   </li>
                                                   <li class=3D"li">
                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p"><a cla=
ss=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepowe=
r/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_syst=
em.html#task_E14666F0D32E45FE820B52C9D3103B6F">Register Smart Licenses</a><=
/p>
                                                     =20
                                                   </li>
                                                </ul>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">If your <spa=
n class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>=
 connects to <span class=3D"ph">Smart Software Manager
                                                      										On-Prem</sp=
an>:
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">See <a class=
=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/=
70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system=
.html#task_F5157FCDC3814D7D9A9D0ED4A87C9488">Configure the Connection to Sm=
art Software Manager On-Prem</a>.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                          </ul>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;12</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Verify that regi=
stration was successful:</p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">In the <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> web in=
terface, go to <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System &gt; Licenses &gt; Smart=
 Licenses</span>. <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Product Registration</span> =
should show a green checkmark.=20
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;13</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">If you have not =
yet done so, add your devices to the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">=
Firepower Management Center</span></span> as managed devices.
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xr=
ef" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/con=
figuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/device_management_basics.html#ID-224=
2-0000069d">Add a Device to the FMC</a></p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;14</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Assign licenses =
to your managed <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defe=
nse</span></span> devices:
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xr=
ef" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/con=
figuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#=
id_75162">Assign Licenses to Multiple Managed Devices</a></p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;15</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Verify that lice=
nses have successfully been added to your devices.</p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xr=
ef" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/con=
figuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#=
task_E06E766894744E2B81D476F727569502">View FTD Licenses and License Status=
</a>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;16</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">As applicable, s=
et up licensing for high-availability and clustered deployments: </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <ul class=3D"ul">
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">For <span cl=
ass=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s in=
 a high availability pair:
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">See the prer=
equisites to <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/doc=
s/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/firepower=
_management_center_high_availability.html#ID-2242-0000039a">Establishing Fi=
repower Management Center High Availability</a>.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">After you co=
nfigure FMC high-availability pairs, device licenses are automatically tran=
sferred from the active to the standby
                                                   management center. You d=
o not need to configure anything specific for licensing.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">For <span cl=
ass=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> device=
s in a high availability pair:
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">Assign the l=
icenses for the features that you want to use to both the active and standb=
y device before you configure high
                                                   availability. If the dev=
ices are licensed for different features, the licenses on the standby devic=
e will be replaced with
                                                   the same set of licenses=
 as the active device.=20
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">For clustere=
d <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></sp=
an> devices:
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">See <a class=
=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/=
70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/clustering_for_the_firepower_t=
hreat_defense.html#id_93999">Licenses for Clustering</a>. Licensing steps a=
re included in <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/d=
ocs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/cluster=
ing_for_the_firepower_threat_defense.html#task_kdw_h5y_c2b">FMC: Add a Clus=
ter</a>.=20
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                          </ul>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>

                              <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                 <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiont=
itle tasklabel cB_Bold">What to do next</h4>

                                    <p class=3D"p">(Optional) If your Firep=
ower Management Center also manages Classic devices (ASA FirePOWER, NGIPSv)=
, configure licensing for
                                       those devices:
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xref" hr=
ef=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configura=
tion/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_494=
77">License Classic Devices (ASA FirePOWER and NGIPSv)</a>.=20
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Understand validity peri=
ods and expiration.  See <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/=
en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v=

                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title10" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"concept_8E207E5F4AB442199B844111=
3DDCD3D3">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title1=
0">Smart Software Manager (CSSM)</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <p class=3D"p">When you purchase one or more Sma=
rt Licenses for Firepower features, you manage them in the Cisco Smart Soft=
ware Manager:
                              <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"http://www.cisco.co=
m/web/ordering/smart-software-manager/index.html" target=3D"_blank">http://=
www.cisco.com/web/ordering/smart-software-manager/index.html</a>. The Smart=
 Software Manager lets you create a primary account for your organization.=
=20
                           </p>
                           <p class=3D"p">By default, your licenses are ass=
igned to the Default Virtual Account under your primary account. As the acc=
ount administrator,
                              you can create additional virtual accounts; f=
or example, for regions, departments, or subsidiaries. Multiple virtual acc=
ounts
                              help you manage large numbers of licenses and=
 appliances.=20
                           </p>
                           <p class=3D"p">You manage licenses
                              		and appliances by virtual account. Only tha=
t virtual account=E2=80=99s appliances can
                              		use the licenses assigned to the account. I=
f you need additional licenses, you
                              		can transfer an unused license from another=
 virtual account. You can also
                              		transfer appliances between virtual account=
s.=20
                              	=20
                           </p>
                           <p class=3D"p">For each virtual account, you can=
 create a
                              			Product Instance Registration Token. Enter=
 this token ID when you deploy each <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">F=
irepower Management Center</span></span>, or when you register an existing =
<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>. You can create a n=
ew token if an existing
                              			token expires. An expired token does not a=
ffect a registered <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> =
that used this token for registration, but you
                              			cannot use an expired token to register a =
<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>. Also, a registered=
 <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> becomes associated=
 with a virtual account based
                              			on the token you use.=20
                           </p>
                           <p class=3D"p">For more information about the Ci=
sco Smart Software Manager, see <span class=3D"ph"><cite class=3D"cite">Cis=
co Smart Software
                                    											Manager User Guide</cite></s=
pan> or <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/buy/smart-a=
ccounts/software-manager.html" target=3D"_blank">https://www.cisco.com/c/en=
/us/buy/smart-accounts/software-manager.html</a> or the online help in CSSM=
, also available from: <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/web/=
fw/softwareworkspace/smartlicensing/SSMCompiledHelps/" target=3D"_blank">ht=
tps://www.cisco.com/web/fw/softwareworkspace/smartlicensing/SSMCompiledHelp=
s/</a>.=20
                           </p>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title11" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"concept_ABB893881EDC494AA5CFA946=
E9A9D156">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title1=
1">Periodic
                           	 Communication with the License Authority
                        </h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <p class=3D"p">In order to maintain your product=
 license entitlement, your product must communicate periodically with the C=
isco License Authority.</p>
                           <p class=3D"p">When you use a Product Instance R=
egistration Token to register a <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firep=
ower Management Center</span></span>, the appliance registers with the Cisc=
o License Authority. The License Authority issues an ID certificate for com=
munication
                              between the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D=
"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> and the License Authority. T=
his certificate is valid for one year, although it will be renewed every si=
x months. If an ID
                              certificate expires (usually in nine months o=
r a year with no communication), the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">=
Firepower Management Center</span></span> reverts to a deregistered state a=
nd licensed features usage become suspended.=20
                           </p>
                           <p class=3D"p">The=20
                              		<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firep=
ower Management Center</span></span>
                              		communicates with the License Authority on =
a periodic basis. If you make
                              		changes in the Smart Software Manager, you =
can refresh the authorization on the
                              	=09
                              		<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firep=
ower Management Center</span></span>
                              		so the changes immediately take effect. You=
 also can wait for the appliance to
                              		communicate as scheduled.=20
                              	=20
                           </p>
                           	=09
                           <p class=3D"p">Your <span class=3D"ph"><span cla=
ss=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> must either have direct=
 Internet access to the License Authority through the Cisco
                              			Smart Software Manager, or use one of the =
options described in <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/u=
s/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/l=
icensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_85794">Licensing Options for Air-Gapp=
ed Deployments</a>. In non-airgapped deployments, normal license
                              			communication occurs every 30 days, but wi=
th the grace period, your appliance will
                              			operate for up to 90 days without calling =
home. You must contact the License Authority
                              			before 90 days have passed.=20
                           </p>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic reference nested2" aria-labell=
edby=3D"ariaid-title12" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_82272">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title1=
2">Service Subscriptions for FTD Features</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body refbody">
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_82272__d2620=
94e1488">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Some features require a servic=
e subscription.</p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">A service subscription enables=
 a specific Firepower feature on a managed device for a set length of time.=
 Service subscriptions
                                 can be purchased in one-, three-, or five-=
year terms. If a subscription expires, Cisco notifies you that you must ren=
ew the
                                 subscription. <span class=3D"ph">If a subs=
cription expires for a <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Thre=
at Defense</span></span> device, you can continue to use the related featur=
es.</span>

                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le14">Base
                              	 Licenses
                           </h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_A0=
0D8504BBA84A27B07B74014AA7337A__section_0106F76557AF401E99930232CAC0D096">
                                 		=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_A00D8504BBA=
84A27B07B74014AA7337A__ID-2240-0000012e">A base license is automatically in=
cluded with every purchase of a <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firep=
ower Threat Defense</span></span> or <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">=
Firepower Threat Defense Virtual</span></span> device. =20
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">The Base license allows you=
 to: </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_A00D85=
04BBA84A27B07B74014AA7337A__li_B118A7CC54F247A1B3B8E2D6465720CA">=20
                                       			=20
                                       <p class=3D"p">configure your=20
                                          				<span class=3D"ph"><span clas=
s=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span>
                                          				devices to perform switching =
and routing (including DHCP relay and NAT)=20
                                          			=20
                                       </p>=20
                                       		 =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">configure <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> devices a=
s a high availability pair
                                       </p>
                                       			=09
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_A00D85=
04BBA84A27B07B74014AA7337A__li_FC10F8E40BF2485FA89BD74DBB0787A4">=20
                                       			=20
                                       <p class=3D"p">configure security mo=
dules as a cluster within a <span class=3D"ph">Firepower 9300</span> chassi=
s (intra-chassis clustering)
                                       </p>=20
                                       		 =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">configure <span class=
=3D"ph">Firepower 9300</span> or <span class=3D"ph">Firepower 4100 series</=
span> devices running <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threa=
t Defense</span></span> as a cluster (inter-chassis clustering)
                                       </p>
                                       			=09
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_A00D85=
04BBA84A27B07B74014AA7337A__li_B9C25F4CF9B543EEBFA7C44F41E418E5">
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">implement user and ap=
plication control by adding user and application conditions to access contr=
ol rules </p>
                                       			=09
                                    </li>
                                 </ul>
                                 		=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">Threat and malware detectio=
n and URL filtering features require additional, optional licenses.</p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph">Except i=
n deployments using Specific License Reservation, </span>Base licenses are =
automatically added to the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower =
Management Center</span></span> for every <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D=
"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> device you register.=20
                                 </p>
                                 		=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">For multi-instance deployme=
nts, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/se=
curity/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the=
_firepower_system.html#id_82182">Licensing for Multi-Instance Deployments</=
a>.
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=20
                              </section>
                           </section>

                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
