C403EA2EA140063">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le15"> Malware Licenses
                              	 for=20
                              	 <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firep=
ower Threat Defense</span></span>
                              	 Devices
                           </h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_A9=
ED087DCFE949168C403EA2EA140063__section_DFDE67C704604FE49A1BF0D7C46753CF">=
=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_A9ED087DCFE=
949168C403EA2EA140063__ID-2240-0000017e">A Malware license for <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> devices a=
llows you to perform Cisco Advanced Malware Protection (AMP) with <span cla=
ss=3D"ph">AMP for Networks</span> and <span class=3D"ph">Cisco Threat Grid<=
/span>. With this feature, you can use <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph=
">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> devices to detect and block malwar=
e in files transmitted over your network. To support this feature license, =
you can purchase
                                    the Malware (AMP) service subscription =
as a stand-alone subscription or in combination with Threat (TM) or Threat =
and URL
                                    Filtering (TMC) subscriptions.
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=
=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                    <tbody><tr>
                                       <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" =
role=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam=
/en/us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                          <section class=3D"note__content">
                                             <hr>=20
                                             		 =20
                                             <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference=
_A9ED087DCFE949168C403EA2EA140063__ID-2240-00000185"><span class=3D"ph"><sp=
an class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span>
                                                			 managed devices with Ma=
lware licenses enabled periodically attempt to connect
                                                			 to the AMP cloud even i=
f you have not configured dynamic analysis. Because of
                                                			 this, the device=E2=80=
=99s Interface Traffic dashboard widget shows transmitted
                                                			 traffic; this is expect=
ed behavior.=20
                                                		 =20
                                             </p>=20
                                             	=09
                                             <hr>
                                          </section>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                 </tbody></table></div>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_A9ED087DCFE=
949168C403EA2EA140063__ID-2240-0000018a">You configure <span class=3D"ph">A=
MP for Networks</span> as part of a file policy, which you then associate w=
ith one or more access control rules. File policies can detect your users
                                    uploading or downloading files of speci=
fic types over specific application protocols. <span class=3D"ph">AMP for N=
etworks</span> allows you to use local malware analysis and file preclassif=
ication to inspect a restricted set of those file types for malware.
                                    You can also download and submit specif=
ic file types to the <span class=3D"ph">Cisco Threat Grid</span> cloud for =
dynamic and Spero analysis to determine whether they contain malware. For t=
hese files, you can view the network
                                    file trajectory, which details the path=
 the file has taken through your network. The Malware license also allows y=
ou to add
                                    specific files to a file list and enabl=
e the file list within a file policy, allowing those files to be automatica=
lly allowed
                                    or blocked on detection.=20
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_A9ED087DCFE=
949168C403EA2EA140063__ID-2240-00000196">If you disable all your Malware li=
censes, the system stops querying the AMP cloud, and also stops acknowledgi=
ng retrospective
                                    events sent from the AMP cloud. You can=
not re-deploy existing access control policies if they include <span class=
=3D"ph">AMP for Networks</span> configurations. Note that for a very brief =
time after a Malware license is disabled, the system can use existing cache=
d file
                                    dispositions. After the time window exp=
ires, the system assigns a disposition of <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"r=
eference_A9ED087DCFE949168C403EA2EA140063__ID-2240-0000019c">Unavailable</c=
ode> to those files.=20
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_A9ED087DCFE=
949168C403EA2EA140063__ID-2240-0000019d">Note that a Malware license is req=
uired only if you deploy <span class=3D"ph">AMP for Networks</span> and <sp=
an class=3D"ph">Cisco Threat Grid</span>. Without a Malware license, the <s=
pan class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></spa=
n> can receive AMP for Endpoints malware events and indications of compromi=
se (IOC) from the AMP cloud.=20
                                 </p>
                                 		=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">See also important informat=
ion at <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/secu=
rity/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/file_policies_a=
nd_advanced_malware_protection.html#id_101648">License Requirements for Fil=
e and Malware Policies</a>.
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title16" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"reference_C38742BBC6364CA7B=
A6F6DA4E3A8C6F7">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le16">Threat
                              	 Licenses
                           </h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_C3=
8742BBC6364CA7BA6F6DA4E3A8C6F7__section_3C0ACEA2F219407BB764D9F53DF19621">=
=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_C38742BBC63=
64CA7BA6F6DA4E3A8C6F7__ID-2240-000000f8">A Threat license allows you to per=
form intrusion detection and
                                    		  prevention, file control, and Secur=
ity Intelligence filtering:=20
                                    	=09
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_C38742=
BBC6364CA7BA6F6DA4E3A8C6F7__li_E7FF3C179336445FA5D4D8F52FE52304">=20
                                       			=20
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_C3874=
2BBC6364CA7BA6F6DA4E3A8C6F7__ID-2240-000000fa"><em class=3D"ph i" id=3D"ref=
erence_C38742BBC6364CA7BA6F6DA4E3A8C6F7__ID-2240-000000fc">Intrusion detect=
ion and prevention</em> allows you to analyze
                                          				network traffic for intrusion=
s and exploits and, optionally, drop offending
                                          				packets.=20
                                          			=20
                                       </p>=20
                                       		 =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_C38742=
BBC6364CA7BA6F6DA4E3A8C6F7__li_DB7D24190B3F45B89A1D221FBD79DC3B">=20
                                       			=20
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_C3874=
2BBC6364CA7BA6F6DA4E3A8C6F7__ID-2240-000000fd"><em class=3D"ph i" id=3D"ref=
erence_C38742BBC6364CA7BA6F6DA4E3A8C6F7__ID-2240-000000ff">File control</em=
> allows you to detect and, optionally, block users from uploading (sending=
) or downloading (receiving) files of specific types
                                          over specific application protoco=
ls. <em class=3D"ph i" id=3D"reference_C38742BBC6364CA7BA6F6DA4E3A8C6F7__ID=
-2240-00000100"><span class=3D"ph">AMP for Networks</span></em>, which requ=
ires a Malware license, allows you to inspect and block a restricted set of=
 those file types based on their dispositions.
                                         =20
                                       </p>=20
                                       		 =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_C38742=
BBC6364CA7BA6F6DA4E3A8C6F7__li_A4BFF1E86902453EB201CB1E653B8DCD">=20
                                       			=20
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_C3874=
2BBC6364CA7BA6F6DA4E3A8C6F7__ID-2240-00000103"><em class=3D"ph i" id=3D"ref=
erence_C38742BBC6364CA7BA6F6DA4E3A8C6F7__ID-2240-00000105">Security Intelli=
gence filtering</em> allows you to block =E2=80=94deny traffic to and from=
=E2=80=94specific IP addresses, URLs, and DNS domain names, before the traf=
fic is subjected
                                          to analysis by access control rul=
es. Dynamic feeds allow you to immediately block connections based on the l=
atest intelligence.
                                          Optionally, you can use a =E2=80=
=9Cmonitor-only=E2=80=9D setting for Security Intelligence filtering.=20
                                       </p>=20
                                       		 =20
                                    </li>
                                 </ul>
                                 		=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">You can purchase a Threat l=
icense as a stand-alone subscription (T) or in combination with URL Filteri=
ng (TC), Malware (TM),
                                    or both (TMC).
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_C38742BBC63=
64CA7BA6F6DA4E3A8C6F7__ID-2240-0000010a">If you disable Threat on managed d=
evices, the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Cent=
er</span></span> stops acknowledging intrusion and file events from the aff=
ected devices. As a consequence, correlation rules that use those
                                    events as a trigger criteria stop firin=
g. Additionally, the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Manage=
ment Center</span></span> will not contact the internet for either Cisco-pr=
ovided or third-party Security Intelligence information. You cannot re-depl=
oy
                                    existing intrusion policies until you r=
e-enable Threat.
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title17" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"reference_0FB126619D0649D79=
B4F666AACE82BAD">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le17">URL Filtering
                              	 Licenses for=20
                              	 <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firep=
ower Threat Defense</span></span>
                              	 Devices
                           </h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_0F=
B126619D0649D79B4F666AACE82BAD__section_94660A4F86DF429297F4AE620ACFBDCF">
                                 		=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_0FB126619D0=
649D79B4F666AACE82BAD__ID-2240-0000015a">The URL Filtering license allows y=
ou to write access control rules that determine the traffic that can traver=
se your network
                                    based on URLs requested by monitored ho=
sts, correlated with information about those URLs. To support this feature =
license,
                                    you can purchase the URL Filtering (URL=
) service subscription as a stand-alone subscription or in combination with=
 Threat
                                    (TC) or Threat and Malware (TMC) subscr=
iptions.
                                 </p>
                                 		=09
                                 <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=
=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                    <tbody><tr>
                                       <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" =
role=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam=
/en/us/td/i/templates/tip.gif"><br><p><b>Tip</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                          <section class=3D"note__content">
                                             <hr>
                                             			=09
                                             <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference=
_0FB126619D0649D79B4F666AACE82BAD__ID-2240-0000015d">Without a URL Filterin=
g license, you can specify individual URLs or groups of URLs to allow or bl=
ock. This gives you granular,
                                                custom control over web tra=
ffic, but does not allow you to use URL category and reputation data to fil=
ter network traffic.
                                               =20
                                             </p>
                                             		=09
                                             <hr>
                                          </section>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                 </tbody></table></div>
                                 		=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_0FB126619D0=
649D79B4F666AACE82BAD__ID-2240-00000160">Although you can add category and =
reputation-based URL conditions to access control rules without a URL Filte=
ring license,
                                    the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"p=
h">Firepower Management Center</span></span> will not download URL informat=
ion. You cannot deploy the access control policy until you first add a URL =
Filtering license
                                    to the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>, then enable it on the de=
vices targeted by the policy.=20
                                 </p>
                                 		=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_0FB126619D0=
649D79B4F666AACE82BAD__ID-2240-00000166">If you disable the URL Filtering l=
icense on managed devices, you may lose access to URL filtering. If your li=
cense expires
                                    or if you disable it, access control ru=
les with URL conditions immediately stop filtering URLs, and your <span cla=
ss=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> can =
no longer download updates to URL data. You cannot re-deploy existing acces=
s control policies if they include rules with
                                    category and reputation-based URL condi=
tions.=20
                                 </p>
                                 	=09
                              </section>
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title18" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_48449">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le18">AnyConnect Licenses</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_48449__se=
ction_lcx_cqr_3z">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">You can use <span class=3D"=
ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> device to con=
figure remote access VPN using the Cisco AnyConnect Secure Mobility Client =
(AnyConnect) and standards-based
                                    IPSec/IKEv2.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">To enable the <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> Remote Ac=
cess VPN feature, you must purchase and enable one of the following license=
s: <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">AnyConnect Plus</span>, <span class=3D"ph u=
icontrol">AnyConnect Apex</span>, or <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">AnyConnec=
t VPN Only</span>. You can use any of the AnyConnect licenses: <span class=
=3D"ph uicontrol">Plus</span>, <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Apex</span>, or=
 <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">VPN Only</span>. You can select <span class=
=3D"ph uicontrol">AnyConnect Plus</span> and <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">A=
nyConnect Apex</span> if you have both licenses and you want to use them bo=
th. The <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Any Connect VPN only</span> license ca=
nnot be used with <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Apex</span> or <span class=
=3D"ph uicontrol">Plus</span>. The AnyConnect license must be shared with t=
he Smart Account. For more instructions, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"http=
://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/products/collateral/security/anyconnect-og.pdf=
" target=3D"_blank">http://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/products/collateral/se=
curity/anyconnect-og.pdf</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">You cannot deploy the Remot=
e Access VPN configuration to the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fir=
epower Threat Defense</span></span> device if the specified device does not=
 have the entitlement for a minimum of one of the specified AnyConnect lice=
nse types.
                                    If the registered license moves out of =
compliance or entitlements expire, the system displays licensing alerts and=
 health
                                    events.=20
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">While using Remote Access V=
PN, your Smart License Account must have the export controlled features (st=
rong encryption) enabled.
                                    The <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"p=
h">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> requires stronger encryption (whi=
ch is higher than DES) for successfully establishing Remote Access VPN conn=
ections with
                                    AnyConnect clients. When you register t=
he device, you must do so with a Smart Software Manager account that is ena=
bled for
                                    export-controlled features. For more in=
formation about export-controlled features, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"h=
ttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/gu=
ide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#reference_59A=
9CDED24034CE2B12D2E633C5C7D2D">FTD License Types and Restrictions</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">You cannot deploy Remote Ac=
cess VPN if the following are true: </p>
                                =20
                                 <ul class=3D"ul" id=3D"id_48449__ul_k2l_xc=
z_hz">
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Smart Licensing on th=
e <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span><=
/span> is running in evaluation mode.=20
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Your Smart Account is=
 not configured to use export-controlled features (strong encryption). Note=
 that you need to reboot <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Th=
reat Defense</span></span> devices after applying a base license that has e=
xport-controlled functionality.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                 </ul>
                                =20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title19" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_81552">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le19">Licensing for Export-Controlled Functionality</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_81552__d2=
62094e2578">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Features =
that require export-controlled functionality</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Certain software features a=
re subject to national security, foreign policy, and anti-terrorism laws an=
d regulations.  These
                                    export-controlled features include:
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Security certificatio=
ns compliance</p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph"><s=
pan class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> Remote Access VPN
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Site to Site VPN with=
 strong encryption</p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">SSH platform policy w=
ith strong encryption</p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">SSL policy with stron=
g encryption</p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Functionality such as=
 SNMPv3 with strong encryption</p>
                                      =20
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                 </ul>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_81552__d2=
62094e2621">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">How to de=
termine whether export-controlled functionality is currently enabled for yo=
ur system</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">To determine whether export=
-controlled functionality is currently enabled for your system: Go to <span=
 class=3D"ph uicontrol">System &gt; Licenses &gt; Smart Licenses</span> and=
 see if <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Export-Controlled Features</span> disp=
lays <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Enabled</span>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_81552__d2=
62094e2638">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">About ena=
bling export-controlled functionality</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">If <span class=3D"ph uicont=
rol">Export-Controlled Features</span> shows <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">D=
isabled</span> and you want to use features that require strong encryption:=
=20
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">There are two ways to enabl=
e strong cryptographic features.  Your organization may be eligible for one=
 or the other (or neither),
                                    but not both.=20
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">If there is <em class=
=3D"ph i">no</em> option to enable export-controlled functionality when you=
 generate a new Product Instance Registration Token in Cisco Smart
                                          Software Manager (CSSM):
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Contact your account =
representative. </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">The <span class=3D"ph=
"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> allows you t=
o use export-controlled features if your Smart Account is eligible for expo=
rt-controlled functionality. When
                                          approved by Cisco, an export cont=
rol license is added to your virtual account and you can use the export-con=
trolled features.
                                          For more information, see <a clas=
s=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower=
/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_syste=
m.html#id_80874">Enabling the Export Control Feature (for Accounts Without =
Global Permission)</a></p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">If the option to use =
export-controlled functionality appears when you generate a new Product Ins=
tance Registration Token in
                                          Cisco Smart Software Manager:
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                      =20
                                       <ul class=3D"ul">
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">The entitlement=
 is perpetual and does not require a subscription.</p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">In order to use=
 export-controlled functionality, your Smart Account must be enabled for th=
is functionality before you license
                                                your <span class=3D"ph"><sp=
an class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>.=20
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">After export-co=
ntrolled functionality is enabled for your Smart Account in <span class=3D"=
ph">Cisco Smart Software Manager</span> (CSSM), you must re-register your <=
span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></sp=
an> using a new Product Instance Registration Token.=20
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">When you create=
 the new Product Instance Registration Token, you must select the option =
=E2=80=9CAllow export-controlled functionality
                                                on the products registered =
with this token.=E2=80=9D This option is enabled by default if this functio=
nality is permitted for your
                                                Smart Account. =20
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">After you insta=
ll a token with export-controlled functionality on your <span class=3D"ph">=
<span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> and assign the=
 relevant licenses to managed <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepow=
er Threat Defense</span></span> devices:=20
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                             <ul class=3D"ul">
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Reboot ea=
ch device to make the newly-enabled features available. </p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">In a high=
 availability deployment, the active and standby devices must be rebooted t=
ogether to avoid an Active-Active condition.</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                             </ul>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                       </ul>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                 </ul>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_81552__d2=
62094e2741">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">More Info=
rmation </h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">For general information abo=
ut export controls, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/e=
n/us/about/legal/global-export-trade.html" target=3D"_blank">https://www.ci=
sco.com/c/en/us/about/legal/global-export-trade.html</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title20" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_86483">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le20">Licensing for High-Availability Configurations</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_86483__d2=
62094e2788">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">See:</p>
                                =20
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">For Firepower Managem=
ent Center appliances in a high-availability pair:</p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p"><a class=3D"xref" hre=
f=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configurat=
ion/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/firepower_management_center_high_availabili=
ty.html#id_21090">License Requirements for FMC High Availability Configurat=
ions</a></p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">For Firepower Threat =
Defense devices in a high-availability pair:</p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p"><a class=3D"xref" hre=
f=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configurat=
ion/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/high_availability_for_firepower_threat_defe=
nse.html#id_21494">License Requirements for FTD Devices in a High Availabil=
ity Pair</a></p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                 </ul>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">See also the topics for spe=
cific license types under the <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.c=
om/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-gu=
ide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#reference_59A9CDED24034CE2B12D2=
E633C5C7D2D">FTD License Types and Restrictions</a> topic.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title21" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_94657">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le21">Licensing for FTD Clusters</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_94657__d2=
62094e2859">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">In addition to information =
in this Licensing chapter, see: </p>
                                =20
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p"><a class=3D"xref" hre=
f=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configurat=
ion/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/clustering_for_the_firepower_threat_defense=
.html#id_93999">Licenses for Clustering</a></p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p"><a class=3D"xref" hre=
f=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configurat=
ion/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/clustering_for_the_firepower_threat_defense=
.html#task_kdw_h5y_c2b">FMC: Add a Cluster</a>.=20
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                 </ul>
                                =20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title22" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_82182">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le22">Licensing for Multi-Instance Deployments</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_82182__d2=
62094e2918">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">All licenses apply per secu=
rity engine/chassis (for the Firepower 4100) or per security module (for th=
e Firepower 9300),=20
                                    not per container instance.=20
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_82182__d2=
62094e2923">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Base Lice=
nses</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Each security engine or mod=
ule consumes a single Base license, which is automatically assigned for all=
 deployments except
                                    those using Specific License Reservatio=
n.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_82182__d2=
62094e2931">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle"><span cla=
ss=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> Virt=
ual
                                 </h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">One entitlement is required=
 for each security engine/module managed by a <span class=3D"ph"><span clas=
s=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> virtual appliance.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_82182__d2=
62094e2946">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Feature L=
icenses</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Each feature you license (M=
alware, Threat, URL Filtering, AnyConnect Apex, AnyConnect Plus, and AnyCon=
nect VPN Only) requires
                                    one license per security engine/module.=
 All instances on the engine/module can share the same feature licenses.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">You must assign the license=
 to each instance.</p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_82182__d2=
62094e2957">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">High-Avai=
lability Deployments</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Instances in a high-availab=
ility pair cannot share feature licenses with each other, but each instance=
 may share feature licenses
                                    with other instances on its respective =
engine/module.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                =20
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_82182__d2=
62094e2965">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Licensing=
 Example</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">To see how the above licens=
ing requirements work together, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.c=
isco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-con=
fig-guide-v70/firepower_threat_defense_logical_devices_for_the.html#id_7898=
2">Licenses for Container Instances</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic task nested2 no_summary_steps"=
 aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title23" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_81767">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title2=
3">Create a Smart Account to Hold Your Licenses</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                           <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"id_8176=
7__d262094e3024">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">A Smart Account is required fo=
r Smart Licenses and can also hold Classic licenses.</p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">You should set up this account=
 before you purchase Smart Licenses.</p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"section prereq p" id=3D"id_817=
67__d262094e3014">
                              <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                 <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiont=
itle tasklabel cB_Bold">Before you begin</h4>
                              </section>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Your account representative or=
 reseller may have set up a Smart Account on your behalf. If so, obtain the=
 necessary information
                                 to access the account from that person ins=
tead of using this procedure, then verify that you can access the account.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">For general information about =
Smart Accounts, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"http://www.cisco.com/go/smart=
accounts" target=3D"_blank">http://www.cisco.com/go/smartaccounts</a>.
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h4>
                           </section>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"st=
epTable" border=3D"0">
                              <tbody>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Request a Smart =
Account:</p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">For instructions, =
see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://community.cisco.com/t5/licensing-ente=
rprise-agreements/request-a-smart-account-for-customers/ta-p/3636515?attach=
ment-id=3D150577" target=3D"_blank">https://community.cisco.com/t5/licensin=
g-enterprise-agreements/request-a-smart-account-for-customers/ta-p/3636515?=
attachment-id=3D150577</a>
                                             .
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">For additional inf=
ormation, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://communities.cisco.com/docs/=
DOC-57261" target=3D"_blank">https://communities.cisco.com/docs/DOC-57261</=
a>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Wait for an emai=
l telling you that your Smart Account is ready to set up. When it arrives, =
click the link it contains, as
                                          directed.
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Set up your Smar=
t Account:</p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Go here: <a class=
=3D"xref" href=3D"https://software.cisco.com/software/company/smartaccounts=
/home?route=3Dmodule/accountcreation" target=3D"_blank">https://software.ci=
sco.com/software/company/smartaccounts/home?route=3Dmodule/accountcreation<=
/a>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">For instructions, =
see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://community.cisco.com/t5/licensing-ente=
rprise-agreements/complete-smart-account-setup-for-customers/ta-p/3636631?a=
ttachment-id=3D132604" target=3D"_blank">https://community.cisco.com/t5/lic=
ensing-enterprise-agreements/complete-smart-account-setup-for-customers/ta-=
p/3636631?attachment-id=3D132604</a>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Verify that you =
can access the account in the Cisco Smart Software Manager (CSSM).</p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Go to <a class=3D"=
xref" href=3D"https://software.cisco.com/#module/SmartLicensing" target=3D"=
_blank">https://software.cisco.com/#module/SmartLicensing</a> and sign in.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <section class=3D"section postreq" id=3D"id_8176=
7__d262094e3076">
                              <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                 <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiont=
itle tasklabel cB_Bold">What to do next</h4>
                              </section>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">If you are following a longer =
workflow, return to the workflow: </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><a class=3D"xref" href=3D"http=
s://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide=
/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_75733">How to=
 License Firepower Threat Defense Devices</a></p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic task nested2 no_summary_steps"=
 aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title24" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_111791">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title2=
4">How to Configure Smart Licensing with Direct Internet Access</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                           <section class=3D"section prereq p" id=3D"id_111=
791__d262094e3118">
                              <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                 <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiont=
itle tasklabel cB_Bold">Before you begin</h4>
                              </section>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">If your deployment is complex =
or you have questions about the licenses you need, see <a class=3D"xref" hr=
ef=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configura=
tion/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_757=
33">How to License Firepower Threat Defense Devices</a>.
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h4>
                           </section>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"st=
epTable" border=3D"0">
                              <tbody>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Obtain a token f=
rom the <span class=3D"ph">Cisco Smart Software Manager</span> licensing po=
rtal.=20
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xr=
ef" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/con=
figuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#=
id_81330">Obtain a Product License Registration Token for Smart Licensing</=
a>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Register your <s=
pan class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></spa=
n> with the Smart licensing portal.
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xr=
ef" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/con=
figuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#=
task_E14666F0D32E45FE820B52C9D3103B6F">Register Smart Licenses</a>.   Be su=
re to address the prerequisites in this topic.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Verify that your=
 FMC registered successfully with the Smart licensing portal.</p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">In the <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> web in=
terface, go to <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System &gt; Licenses &gt; Smart=
 Licenses</span>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph =
uicontrol">Product Registration</span> should show a green checkmark.=20
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">If you have not =
yet done so, add devices to your FMC.</p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xr=
ef" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/con=
figuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/device_management_basics.html#ID-224=
2-0000069d">Add a Device to the FMC</a>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;5</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Assign licenses =
to the devices that are managed by your FMC.</p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xr=
ef" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/con=
figuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#=
id_75162">Assign Licenses to Multiple Managed Devices</a>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;6</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Verify that lice=
nses are successfully installed.</p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xr=
ef" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/con=
figuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#=
task_E06E766894744E2B81D476F727569502">View FTD Licenses and License Status=
</a>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <section class=3D"section postreq" id=3D"id_1117=
91__d262094e3215">
                              <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                 <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiont=
itle tasklabel cB_Bold">What to do next</h4>
                              </section>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">If applicable, set up licensin=
g for high-availability and clustered deployments.</p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">See the final steps in <a clas=
s=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower=
/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_syste=
m.html#id_75733">How to License Firepower Threat Defense Devices</a>.
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                        </section>

                              <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"htt=

2E45FE820B52C9D3103B6F">Register Smart Licenses</a></li>
                              <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guid=
e/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_80874">Enabl=
ing the Export Control Feature (for Accounts Without Global Permission)</a>=
</li>
                              <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guid=
e/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_80874">Disab=
ling the Export Control Feature (for Accounts without Global Permission)</a=
></li>
                           </ul>
                        </nav>
