                        <article class=3D"topic task nested3 no_summary_ste=
ps" aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title25" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_81330">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le25">Obtain a Product License Registration Token for Smart Licensing</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                              <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"id_8=
1330__d262094e3323">
                                =20
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section prereq p" id=3D"id_=
81330__d262094e3280">
                                 <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                    <h5 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"secti=
ontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">Before you begin</h5>
                                 </section>
                                =20
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Create a Smart Accoun=
t, if you have not already done so: Visit <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https:/=
/software.cisco.com/smartaccounts/setup#accountcreation-account" target=3D"=
_blank">https://software.cisco.com/smartaccounts/setup#accountcreation-acco=
unt</a>. For information, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.c=
om/c/en/us/buy/smart-accounts.html" target=3D"_blank">https://www.cisco.com=
/c/en/us/buy/smart-accounts.html</a>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                      =20
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Ensure that you have =
purchased the type and number of licenses you require.</p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Verify that the licen=
ses you need appear in your Smart Account.</p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">If your licenses do n=
ot appear in your Smart Account, ask the person who ordered them (for examp=
le, your Cisco sales representative
                                          or authorized reseller) to transf=
er those licenses to your Smart Account.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Ideally, check the pr=
erequisites for <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/=
docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licens=
ing_the_firepower_system.html#task_E14666F0D32E45FE820B52C9D3103B6F">Regist=
er Smart Licenses</a> to ensure that your registration process goes smoothl=
y.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Make sure you have yo=
ur credentials to sign in to the <span class=3D"ph">Cisco Smart Software Ma=
nager</span>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                 </ul>
                                =20
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                 <h5 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiont=
itle tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h5>
                              </section>
                              <hr noshade=3D"">
                              <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D=
"stepTable" border=3D"0">
                                 <tbody>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Go to <a clas=
s=3D"xref" href=3D"https://software.cisco.com/" target=3D"_blank">https://s=
oftware.cisco.com</a>.
                                          </p>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <span c=
lass=3D"ph uicontrol">Smart Software Licensing</span> (in the License secti=
on.)
                                          </p>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Sign in to th=
e <span class=3D"ph">Cisco Smart Software Manager</span>.
                                          </p>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <span c=
lass=3D"ph uicontrol">Inventory</span>.
                                          </p>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;5</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <span c=
lass=3D"ph uicontrol">General</span>.
                                          </p>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;6</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <span c=
lass=3D"ph uicontrol">New Token</span>.
                                          </p>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;7</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">For <span cla=
ss=3D"ph uicontrol">Description</span>, enter a name that uniquely and clea=
rly identifies the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Manageme=
nt Center</span></span> for which you will use this token.
                                          </p>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;8</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Enter an expi=
ration time within 365 days.</p>
                                          <section class=3D"itemgroup info"=
>
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">This determines=
 how much time you have to register the token to a <span class=3D"ph"><span=
 class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>. (Your license enti=
tlement term is independent of this setting but may start to count down eve=
n if you have not yet registered
                                                your token.)
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                          </section>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;9</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">If you see an=
 option to enable export-controlled functionality, and you plan to use feat=
ures that require strong encryption,
                                             select this option.=20
                                          </p>
                                          <section class=3D"itemgroup info"=
>
                                            =20
                                             <div class=3D"tableContainer">=
<table class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                                <tbody><tr>
                                                   <td width=3D"1%" class=
=3D"td_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                      <p><b>Important</b></=
p>&nbsp;
                                                   </td>
                                                   <td border=3D"0" class=
=3D"td_faq">
                                                      <section class=3D"not=
e__content">
                                                        =20
                                                         <p class=3D"p">If =
you see this option, you must select it now if you plan to use this functio=
nality.  You cannot enable export-controlled
                                                            functionality l=
ater. =20
                                                         </p>
                                                        =20
                                                         <p class=3D"p">If =
you do not see this option, and your organization has obtained a license fo=
r export-controlled functionality, you will
                                                            enable this fun=
ctionality later, as described in <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cis=
co.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-confi=
g-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_80874">Enabling the Expo=
rt Control Feature (for Accounts Without Global Permission)</a>.=20
                                                         </p>
                                                        =20
                                                        =20
                                                      </section>
                                                   </td>
                                                </tr>
                                             </tbody></table></div>
                                            =20
                                          </section>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;10</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <span c=
lass=3D"ph uicontrol">Create Token</span>.
                                          </p>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;11</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Locate your n=
ew token in the list and click <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Actions</span>,=
 then choose <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Copy</span> or <span class=3D"ph =
uicontrol">Download</span>.
                                          </p>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;12</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">If necessary,=
 save your token in a safe place until you are ready to enter it into your =
<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></s=
pan>.
                                          </p>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                 </tbody>
                              </table></div>
                              <hr noshade=3D"">
                              <section class=3D"section postreq" id=3D"id_8=
1330__d262094e3429">
                                 <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                    <h5 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"secti=
ontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">What to do next</h5>
                                 </section>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Continue with the steps in =
<a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/fi=
repower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepowe=
r_system.html#task_E14666F0D32E45FE820B52C9D3103B6F">Register Smart License=
s</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic task nested3 no_summary_ste=
ps" aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title26" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"task_E14666F0D3=
2E45FE820B52C9D3103B6F">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le26">Register Smart Licenses</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                              <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"task=
_E14666F0D32E45FE820B52C9D3103B6F__context_EAD8DC84A42944FCB202E57BFA9784E0=
">
                                 		=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">Register the <span class=3D=
"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> with the =
Cisco Smart Software Manager.
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section prereq p" id=3D"tas=
k_E14666F0D32E45FE820B52C9D3103B6F__prereq_0F8BA40C5A5B4F8F929D0C2D657ADEB4=
">
                                 <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                    <h5 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"secti=
ontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">Before you begin</h5>
                                 </section>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">If your deployment is=
 air-gapped, do not use this procedure. Instead, see <a class=3D"xref" href=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configurati=
on/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#task_F51=
57FCDC3814D7D9A9D0ED4A87C9488">Configure the Connection to Smart Software M=
anager On-Prem</a><span class=3D"ph"> or <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://=
www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpm=
c-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_80591">How to Imp=
lement Specific License Reservation</a>, respectively</span>.
                                       </p>
                                       			=09
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">Ensure that the <span=
 class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> =
can reach the Cisco Smart Software Manager (CSSM) server at tools.cisco.com=
:443.
                                       </p>
                                       				=09
                                       			=09
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_E14666F0D32=
E45FE820B52C9D3103B6F__li_B4EDED8168054220ACC4EBA967D5FC86">=20
                                       			=20
                                       <p class=3D"p"> Make sure the NTP da=
emon is running on your=20
                                          				<span class=3D"ph"><span clas=
s=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>.
                                          				During registration, a key ex=
change occurs between the NTP server and the Cisco
                                          				Smart Software Manager, so ti=
me must be in sync for proper registration.
                                          			=20
                                       </p>
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">If you are deploying =
<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span=
> on a Firepower 4100/9300 chassis, you must configure NTP on the Firepower
                                          						chassis using the same NTP =
server for the chassis as for the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fir=
epower Management Center</span></span>.
                                       </p>=20
                                       		 =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">If your organization =
has multiple <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Cen=
ter</span></span> appliances, make sure each FMC has a unique name that cle=
arly identifies and distinguishes it from other <span class=3D"ph"><span cl=
ass=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> appliances that may be=
 registered to the same virtual account. This name is critical for managing=
 your Smart License entitlements
                                          and ambiguous names will lead to =
problems later.=20
                                       </p>
                                       			=09
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">Generate the necessar=
y product license registration token from the <span class=3D"ph">Cisco Smar=
t Software Manager</span>.  See <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco=
.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-=
guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_81330">Obtain a Product Li=
cense Registration Token for Smart Licensing</a>, including all prerequisit=
es. Make sure the token is accessible from the machine from which you will =
access your <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Cent=
er</span></span>.
                                       </p>
                                       			=09
                                    </li>
                                 </ul>=20
                                 	=20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                 <h5 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiont=
itle tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h5>
                              </section>
                              <hr noshade=3D"">
                              <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D=
"stepTable" border=3D"0">
                                 <tbody>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"task_E14666=
F0D32E45FE820B52C9D3103B6F__step_C49A3FACB53042EFBD491854F7D6EE40">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Choose <span =
class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Sy=
stem</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Licenses</span> &gt; <span cl=
ass=3D"ph uicontrol">Smart Licenses</span></span></span>.=20
                                          </p>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"task_E14666=
F0D32E45FE820B52C9D3103B6F__step_0974D832BBC145DA8725B90A957F18B7">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <span c=
lass=3D"ph uicontrol">Register</span>.=20
                                          </p>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"task_E14666=
F0D32E45FE820B52C9D3103B6F__step_8B282F9C190344B295E25C7C2FB3E9D9">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Paste the tok=
en you generated from <span class=3D"ph">Cisco Smart Software Manager</span=
> into the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"task_E14666F0D32E45FE820B52C9=
D3103B6F__ID-2240-00000314">Product Instance Registration Token</span> fiel=
d.
                                          </p>
                                          <section class=3D"itemgroup info"=
>
                                             				=09
                                             <p class=3D"p">Make sure there=
 are no empty spaces or blank lines at the beginning or end of the text.</p=
>
                                             			=09
                                          </section>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Decide whethe=
r to send usage data to Cisco.</p>
                                          <section class=3D"itemgroup info"=
>
                                             				=09
                                             <ul class=3D"ul">
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                   						=09
                                                   <p class=3D"p"><span cla=
ss=3D"ph uicontrol">Enable Cisco Success Network</span> is enabled by defau=
lt. You can click <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">sample data</span> to see th=
e kind of data Cisco collects. To help you make your decision, read the Cis=
co Success Network information block.
                                                   </p>
                                                   					=09
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                   						=09
                                                   <p class=3D"p"><span cla=
ss=3D"ph uicontrol">Enable Cisco Proactive Support</span> is enabled by def=
ault. You can review the kind of data Cisco collects in the link provided a=
bove the check box. To help you
                                                      make your decision, r=
ead the Cisco Support Diagnostics information block.
                                                   </p>
                                                   						=09
                                                   <table class=3D"olh_note=
" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                                      <tbody><tr>
                                                         <td width=3D"1%" c=
lass=3D"td_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                            <p><b>Note</b><=
/p>&nbsp;
                                                         </td>
                                                         <td border=3D"0" c=
lass=3D"td_faq">
                                                            <section class=
=3D"note__content">
                                                               							=09
                                                               <ul class=3D=
"ul">
                                                                  <li class=
=3D"li">
                                                                     						=
			=09
                                                                     <p cla=
ss=3D"p">When enabled, Cisco Support Diagnostics is enabled in the <span cl=
ass=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> (<span=
 class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span>) de=

>

<table class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">

=3D"td_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                      <p><b>Note</b></p>&nb=
sp;

                                                   <td border=3D"0" class=
=3D"td_faq">

e__content">

                                                         <p class=3D"p">If =
you see the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Request Export Key</span>, your ac=
count is approved for the export-controlled functionality and you can proce=
ed to use the required feature.

>

=3D"td_faq">

e__content">

the export control key request fails, make sure that your virtual account h=
as a valid Export Control license. </p>

0874__d262094e3906">
                                 <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                    <h5 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"secti=
ontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">What to do next</h5>
                                 </section>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">You can now deploy configur=
ations or policies that use the export-controlled features.</p>
                                =20
                                 <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=
=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                    <tbody><tr>
                                       <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" =
role=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam=
/en/us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Remember</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                          <section class=3D"note__content">
                                             <hr>
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">The new export-=
controlled licenses and all features enabled by it do not take effect on th=
e <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></sp=
an> devices until the devices are rebooted. Until then, only the features s=
upported by the older license will be active.=20
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">In high-availab=
ility deployments both the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower =
Threat Defense</span></span> devices need to be rebooted simultaneously, to=
 avoid an Active-Active condition.
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                             <hr>
                                          </section>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                 </tbody></table></div>
                                =20
                              </section>
                           </section>

></nav>

0874__d262094e3966">

                                 <p class=3D"p">If you enabled the export-c=
ontrolled functionality using the feature described in <a class=3D"xref" hr=
ef=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configura=
tion/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_808=
74">Enabling the Export Control Feature (for Accounts Without Global Permis=
sion)</a>, you can disable this functionality using this procedure.=20
                                 </p>

itle tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h5>

"stepTable" border=3D"0">

rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Choose <span =
class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span> &gt; <s=
pan class=3D"ph uicontrol">Licenses</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol=
"> Smart Licenses </span></span>.
                                          </p>
                                          <section class=3D"itemgroup info"=
>
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">This releases t=
he license back into the pool of available licenses in your virtual account=
, where it is now available for
                                                reuse.
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                          </section>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd"> Disable the =
export control license by clicking <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Return Expo=
rt Key</span>.
                                          </p>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                 </tbody>
                              </table></div>

urity/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_=

                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title30" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_79843">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title3=
0"><span class=3D"ph">Smart Software Manager
                              										On-Prem</span> Overview
                        </h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <p class=3D"p">As described in <a class=3D"xref"=
 href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/config=
uration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#con=
cept_ABB893881EDC494AA5CFA946E9A9D156">Periodic Communication with the Lice=
nse Authority</a>, your system must communicate regularly with Cisco to mai=
ntain your license entitlement. If you have one of the following
                              situations, you might want to use a <span cla=
ss=3D"ph">Smart Software Manager
                                 										On-Prem</span> (also known as <s=
pan class=3D"ph">SSM On-Prem</span>, and formerly known as "Smart Software =
Satellite Server") as a proxy for connections to the License Authority:=20
                           </p>
                           <ul class=3D"ul">
                              <li class=3D"li" id=3D"id_79843__li_5F1A37DD6=
4D8493BA2DC34C07F5A2718">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Your <span class=3D"ph"><sp=
an class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> is offline or oth=
erwise has limited or no connectivity (in other words, is deployed in an ai=
r-gapped network.)=20
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">(For an alternate solution =
for air-gapped networks, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.co=
m/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-gui=
de-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_85794">Licensing Options for =
Air-Gapped Deployments</a>.)=20
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li" id=3D"id_79843__li_5FDAE2FC0=
10E43359E98C5A2038C5F30">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Your <span class=3D"ph"><sp=
an class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> has permanent con=
nectivity, but you want to manage your Smart Licenses via a single connecti=
on from your network.=20
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                           </ul>
                           <p class=3D"p">Cisco <span class=3D"ph">Smart So=
ftware Manager
                                 										On-Prem</span> allows you to sch=
edule synchronization or manually synchronize Smart License authorization w=
ith the Smart Software Manager.
                             =20
                           </p>
                           <p class=3D"p">For more information about <span =
class=3D"ph">Smart Software Manager
                                 										On-Prem</span>, see  <a class=3D=
"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/buy/smart-accounts/software-ma=
nager.html#~on-prem" target=3D"_blank">https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/buy/sm=
art-accounts/software-manager.html#~on-prem</a>
                             =20
                           </p>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links">
                           <ul class=3D"ullinks">
                              <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guid=
e/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_79920">How t=
o Deploy Smart Software Manager On-Prem</a></li>
                           </ul>
                        </nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->

ps" aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title31" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_79920">

ctiontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">Before you begin</h6>
                                    </section>
                                    		=09
                                    <ul class=3D"ul">
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                          				=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">Set up <span class=
=3D"ph">Smart Software Manager
                                                										On-Prem</span> (<=
span class=3D"ph">SSM On-Prem</span>). For information, see <a class=3D"xre=
f" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/conf=
iguration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#i=
d_79920">How to Deploy Smart Software Manager On-Prem</a>.
                                          </p>
                                          			=09
                                       </li>
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                          				=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">Make a note of the=
 CN of the TLS/SSL certificate on your <span class=3D"ph">SSM On-Prem</span=
>.=20
                                          </p>
                                          			=09
                                       </li>
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                          				=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">Verify that your F=
MC can reach your <span class=3D"ph">SSM On-Prem</span>. For example, verif=
y that the FQDN configured as the <span class=3D"ph">SSM On-Prem</span> cal=
l-home URL can be resolved by your internal DNS server.=20
                                          </p>
                                          			=09
                                       </li>
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                          				=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">Go to <a class=3D"=
xref" href=3D"http://www.cisco.com/security/pki/certs/clrca.cer" target=3D"=
_blank">http://www.cisco.com/security/pki/certs/clrca.cer</a> and copy the =
entire body of the TLS/SSL certificate (from "-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----" =
to "-----END CERTIFICATE-----") into
                                             a place you can access during =
configuration.

n class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span> &gt; =
<span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Integration</span></span></span>.

oken. </p>

                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title33" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_79548">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title3=
3">Specific License Reservation (SLR)</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <p class=3D"p">You can use the Specific License =
Reservation feature to deploy Smart Licensing in an air-gapped network.</p>
                          =20
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"ol=
h_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                              <tbody><tr>
                                 <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=
=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/=
us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                    <section class=3D"note__content">
                                       <hr>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Various names are use=
d at Cisco for Specific License Reservation, including SLR, SPLR, PLR, and =
Permanent License Reservation.
                                          These terms may also be used at C=
isco to refer to similar but not necessarily identical licensing models.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <hr>
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody></table></div>
                           <p class=3D"p">When Specific License Reservation=
 is enabled, the Firepower Management Center reserves licenses from your vi=
rtual account
                              for a specified duration without accessing th=
e Cisco Smart Software Manager or using <span class=3D"ph">Smart Software M=
anager
                                 										On-Prem</span>.
                           </p>
                           <p class=3D"p">Your Firepower Management Center =
can also simultaneously manage devices that use standard Classic licenses. =
However, those
                              devices do not use Specific License Reservati=
on.
                           </p>
                           <p class=3D"p">Features that require access to t=
he internet, such as URL Lookups or contextual cross-launch to public web s=
ites, will not
                              work.
                           </p>
                           <p class=3D"p">Cisco does not collect web analyt=
ics or telemetry data for deployments that use Specific License Reservation=
.</p>
                           <p class=3D"p">Related Topics:</p>
                           <ul class=3D"ul">
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p"><a class=3D"xref" href=3D"h=
ttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/gu=
ide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_86229">Bes=
t Practices for Specific License Reservation</a></p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p"><a class=3D"xref" href=3D"h=
ttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/gu=
ide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_79532">Req=
uirements for Specific License Reservation</a></p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p"><a class=3D"xref" href=3D"h=
ttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/gu=
ide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_80591">How=
 to Implement Specific License Reservation</a></p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p"><a class=3D"xref" href=3D"h=
ttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/gu=
ide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_79535">Spe=
cific License Reservation Status</a></p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p"><a class=3D"xref" href=3D"h=
ttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/gu=
ide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_79540">Upd=
ate a Specific License Reservation</a></p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p"><a class=3D"xref" href=3D"h=
ttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/gu=
ide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_79541">Dea=
ctivate and Return the Specific License Reservation</a></p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p"><a class=3D"xref" href=3D"h=
ttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/gu=
ide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_84365">Tro=
ubleshoot Specific License Reservation</a></p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                           </ul>
                        </section>
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title34" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_86229">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le34">Best Practices for Specific License Reservation</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_86229__d2=
62094e4721">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">You will not be able to suc=
cessfully implement Specific License Reservation without reading this docum=
entation. </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">An unsuccessful attempt is =
likely to result in the need to contact TAC. </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">To avoid problems, follow t=
he instructions carefully, including the prerequisites and verification pro=
cedures.</p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                        </article>

elledby=3D"ariaid-title35" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_79532">

le35">Requirements for Specific License Reservation</h4>

62094e4742">

                                 <p class=3D"p">Usage of Specific License R=

href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configu=
ration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_8=
2312">Prerequisites for Specific License Reservation</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                        </article>

                           <article class=3D"topic reference nested4" aria-=
labelledby=3D"ariaid-title37" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_82312">
                              <h5 class=3D"title topictitle5" id=3D"ariaid-=
title37">Prerequisites for Specific License Reservation</h5>
                              <section class=3D"body refbody">
                                 <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_82312_=
_d262094e4916">
                                   =20
                                    <ul class=3D"ul">
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Set up your Smart =
Account.</p>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xr=
ef" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/con=
figuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#=
id_81767">Create a Smart Account to Hold Your Licenses</a>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </li>
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">If you are current=
ly using standard Smart Licensing on your <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D=
"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>, de-register the <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> before=
 you implement Specific License Reservation. For information, see <a class=
=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/=
70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system=
.html#task_E9C821FFDC2A4958A3A5F536E89EB895">Deregister a Firepower Managem=
ent Center from the Cisco Smart Software Manager</a>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">All Smart Licenses=
 that are currently deployed to your Firepower Management Center will be re=
turned to the pool of available
                                             licenses in your account, and =
you can re-use them when you implement Specific License Reservation.=20
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </li>
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Specific License R=
eservation requires the same number and types of licenses as standard Smart=
 Licensing.  Determine how many
                                             standard licenses and service =
subscriptions you need for the devices and features you will deploy. Be sur=
e to include entitlements
                                             for <span class=3D"ph"><span c=
lass=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> Virtual if applicable=
.=20
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">For descriptions o=
f Firepower licenses and service subscriptions, see <a class=3D"xref" href=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configurati=
on/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#referenc=
e_59A9CDED24034CE2B12D2E633C5C7D2D">FTD License Types and Restrictions</a> =
and its subtopics, especially <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.c=
om/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-gu=
ide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#reference_32D26DAA9C3445008CD8E=
72E598191E3">Firepower Management Center Virtual Licenses</a>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </li>
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Purchase the licen=
ses you need.</p>
                                         =20
                                       </li>
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Arrange for export=
-controlled strong cryptographic functionality, if required and if your org=
anization is eligible. Confirm
                                             that your account is enabled t=
o use it, or the required per-Firepower Management Center licenses appear i=
n your virtual account.
                                             Your account representative ca=
n assist you with this.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">For more informati=
on, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/sec=
urity/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_=
firepower_system.html#id_81552">Licensing for Export-Controlled Functionali=
ty</a>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </li>
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Work with your acc=
ount representative to obtain approval for Specific License Reservation (SL=
R) for your Firepower products.</p>
                                         =20
                                       </li>
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Obtain confirmatio=
n from your account representative that the Specific License Reservation is=
 ready for use and reflected
                                             in your Smart Account.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </li>
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Add managed device=
s to your Firepower Management Center. For instructions, see <a class=3D"xr=
ef" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/con=
figuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/device_management_basics.html#ID-224=
2-0000069d">Add a Device to the FMC</a>. (You can add managed devices at an=
y time, but adding them now simplifes this process.) You will need to enabl=
e the evaluation
                                             license in order to do this (u=
nder <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System &gt; Licenses &gt; Smart Licenses<=
/span>). Evaluation licensing does not require a connection to the License =
Authority.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </li>
                                      =20
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Make sure NTP is c=
onfigured on the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management=
 Center</span></span> and managed devices. Time must be synchronized
                                             for registration to succeed.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">If you are deployi=
ng FTD on a Firepower 4100/9300
                                             chassis, you must configure NT=
P on the Firepower
                                             chassis using the same NTP ser=
ver for the chassis as
                                             for the <span class=3D"ph"><sp=
an class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </li>
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">(Recommended) If y=
ou will deploy a <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management=
 Center</span></span> pair in a high availability configuration, configure =
that before you assign licenses. (FMCs in a high availability configuration
                                             require the same number of lic=
enses as a single FMC.) If you have already deployed licenses to the second=
ary appliance, de-register
                                             licensing from that appliance.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </li>
                                    </ul>
                                   =20
                                 </section>
                              </section>
                           </article>
                           <article class=3D"topic task nested4 no_summary_=
steps" aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title38" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_81308">
                              <h5 class=3D"title topictitle5" id=3D"ariaid-=
title38">Verify that your Smart Account is Ready to Deploy Specific License=
 Reservation</h5>

d_81308__d262094e5068">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">In order to prevent prob=
lems when deploying your Specific License Reservation, complete this proced=
ure before you make any
                                       changes in your <span class=3D"ph"><=
span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>.

id_81308__d262094e5047">

                                       <h6 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"se=
ctiontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">Before you begin</h6>

                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Ensure that you ha=
ve met the requirements described in <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.=
cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-co=
nfig-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_82312">Prerequisites =
for Specific License Reservation</a>.
                                          </p>

                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Make sure you have=
 your <span class=3D"ph">Cisco Smart Software Manager</span> credentials.
                                          </p>
                                         =20

                                    </ul>

ontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h6>

=3D"stepTable" border=3D"0">

 border=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

                                          <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top"=
 border=3D"0">

 the <span class=3D"ph">Cisco Smart Software Manager</span>:

fo">

xref" href=3D"https://software.cisco.com/#SmartLicensing-Inventory" target=
=3D"_blank">https://software.cisco.com/#SmartLicensing-Inventory</a></p>
                                               =20
                                             </section>

 border=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                             <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                          </td>
                                          <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top"=
 border=3D"0">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">If applica=
ble, select the correct account from the top right corner of the page.</p>
                                          </td>

                                          <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top"=
 border=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                             <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                          </td>
                                          <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top"=
 border=3D"0">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">If necessa=
ry, click <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Inventory</span>.

                                          </td>
                                       </tr>
                                       <tr class=3D"li step">
                                          <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top"=
 border=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                             <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                          </td>
                                          <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top"=
 border=3D"0">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <spa=
n class=3D"ph uicontrol">Licenses</span>.
                                             </p>

                                       </tr>
                                       <tr class=3D"li step">
                                          <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top"=
 border=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                             <p><b>Step&nbsp;5</b></p>
                                          </td>
                                          <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top"=
 border=3D"0">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">Verify the=
 following: </p>

fo">
                                               =20
                                                <ul class=3D"ul">

                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p">There =
is a <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">License Reservation</span> button.
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                   </li>
                                                   <li class=3D"li">
                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p">There =
are enough platform and feature licenses for the devices and features you w=
ill deploy, including Firepower Management
                                                         Center Virtual ent=
itlements for your devices, if applicable.
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                   </li>
                                                </ul>
                                               =20
                                             </section>
                                          </td>
                                       </tr>
                                       <tr class=3D"li step">

 border=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                             <p><b>Step&nbsp;6</b></p>
                                          </td>
                                          <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top"=
 border=3D"0">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">If any of =
these items is missing or incorrect, contact your account representative to=

fo">

r"><table class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">

s=3D"td_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">

></p>&nbsp;

s=3D"td_faq">

note__content">

Do <strong class=3D"ph b">not</strong> continue with this process until any=
 problems are corrected.

                                                      </td>
                                                   </tr>
                                                </tbody></table></div>

                                          </td>

he "Smart Licenses" menu option to "Specific Licenses" in Firepower Managem=
ent Center.</p>

=3D"stepTable" border=3D"0">

 border=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

 border=3D"0">

 Firepower Management Center console using a USB keyboard and VGA monitor, =
or use SSH to access the management interface.

 border=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

                                          <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top"=
 border=3D"0">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">Log into t=
he Firepower Management Center using the CLI<strong class=3D"ph b">admin</s=
trong> account. <span class=3D"ph">This give you access
                                                   to the Firepower Managem=
ent Center CLI.</span></p>

 border=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

 border=3D"0">

s=3D"ph">Enter
                                                   the <span><span class=3D=
"keyword kwd">expert</span> </span> command to access the Linux

 border=3D"0">

9537__enableslr">Execute the following command to access the Specific Licen=
se Reservation options: </p>

fo">

=3D"keyword cmdname">sudo manage_slr.pl</span></p>

epxmp">

">

 class=3D"sectiontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">Example:</h6>
                                                </section>
                                                <pre class=3D"pre codeblock=
"><code>admin@fmc63betaslr: ~$ sudo manage_slr.pl
Password:


**************** Configuration Utility **************

1   Show SLR Status
2   Enable SLR
3   Disable SLR
0   Exit

**************************************************************
Enter choice: </code></pre>
                                                </section>
                                          </td>
                                       </tr>
                                       <tr class=3D"li step">

 border=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

                                          <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top"=
 border=3D"0">

cific License Reservation by selecting option 2. </p>

 border=3D"0">

ion 0 to exit the manage_slr utility.</p>

 border=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

 border=3D"0">

><span class=3D"keyword kwd">exit</span> </span> to exit the Linux shell.

 border=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                             <p><b>Step&nbsp;8</b></p>

                                          <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top"=
 border=3D"0">

s=3D"ph">Enter</span>

d kwd">exit</span> </span> to exit the command line interface.

                                       <tr class=3D"li step">
                                          <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top"=
 border=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

 border=3D"0">

t you can access the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Specific License Reservat=
ion</span> page in the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Mana=
gement Center</span></span> web interface:

fo">

                                                <ul class=3D"ul">

                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p">If the=
 <span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span><=
/span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Lic=
enses</span></span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph u=
icontrol">Smart Licenses</span></span> page is currently displayed, refresh=
 the page.=20
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                   </li>
                                                   <li class=3D"li">
                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p">Otherw=
ise, choose <span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Sys=
tem</span></span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uic=
ontrol">Licenses</span></span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span cl=
ass=3D"ph uicontrol">Specific Licenses</span></span>.=20
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                   </li>
                                                </ul>
                                               =20
                                             </section>
                                          </td>
                                       </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                 </table></div>
                                 <hr noshade=3D"">
                              </section>

fo">

xref" href=3D"https://software.cisco.com/#SmartLicensing-Inventory" target=

 code that you generated from Firepower Management Center into the <span cl=

">

                              <h5 class=3D"title topictitle5" id=3D"ariaid-=
title43">Assign Specific Licenses to Managed Devices</h5>
                              <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                                 <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"i=
d_79539__d262094e5537">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Use this procedure to qu=
ickly assign licenses to multiple managed devices at one time.</p>
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">You can also use this pr=
ocedure to disable or move licenses from one Firepower Threat Defense devic=
e to another. If you disable
                                       a license for a device, you cannot u=
se the features associated with that license on that device.
                                    </p>

ontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h6>

=3D"stepTable" border=3D"0">

 border=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

 border=3D"0">

pan class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">=
Licenses</span> &gt;<span class=3D"ph uicontrol"> Specific Licenses</span>.

 border=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

 tab and assign licenses to devices as needed.</p>

EC4768457A7544F4B51493E23CB346AA">

9540__d262094e5608">

 deployed Specific Licenses on your Firepower Management Center, you can ad=
d or remove entitlements
                                    at any time using this procedure.

itle tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h5>

"stepTable" border=3D"0">

rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

rder=3D"0">

Management Center, obtain the unique product instance identifier of this ap=
pliance: </p>

ps">

pexpand">

pexpand">

 info">

need this value several times during this process.</p>

                                                </section>

                                          </ol>

rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

he Cisco Smart Software Manager: </p>

 info">

=3D"xref" href=3D"https://software.cisco.com/#SmartLicensing-Inventory" tar=
get=3D"_blank">https://software.cisco.com/#SmartLicensing-Inventory</a></p>

pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">If nece=
ssary, click <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Inventory</span>.

 info">

                                                   <p class=3D"p">(This pag=
e may display automatically.)</p>

                                                </section>

pexpand">

                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <=
span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Product Instances</span>.

pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Look fo=
r a product instance that has <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">FP</span> in the=
 <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Type</span> column and a generic SKU (not a h=
ostname) in the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Name</span> column. You may al=
so be able to use the values in other table columns to help determine which=

                                                   is the correct Firepower=
 Management Center. Click the name.

pexpand">

 the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">UUID</span> and see if it is the UUID of =

 info">

ou must repeat these steps until you find the correct Firepower Management =
Center.</p>

rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

rder=3D"0">

ps">

pexpand">

page that shows the correct UUID, choose <span class=3D"ph menucascade"><sp=
an class=3D"ph uicontrol">Actions</span></span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph menu=
cascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Update Reserved Licenses</span></span=
>.

pexpand">

the reserved licenses as needed.</p>

 info">

iner"><table class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">

lass=3D"td_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">

</b></p>&nbsp;

lass=3D"td_faq">

=3D"note__content">
                                                              =20
                                                               <ul class=3D=
"ul">
                                                                  <li class=
=3D"li">
                                                                    =20
                                                                    =20
                                                                     <p cla=
ss=3D"p">You must explicitly include a <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Firepow=
er Threat Defense Base Features</span> license for each managed device, or,=
 for multi-instance deployments, a <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Firepower T=
hreat Defense Base Features</span> license for each module.
                                                                     </p>
                                                                    =20
                                                                  </li>
                                                                  <li class=
=3D"li">
                                                                    =20
                                                                     <p cla=
ss=3D"p">If you are using a virtual management center, you must include a <=
span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Firepower MCv Device License</span> entitlement=
 for each module (in multi-instance deployments) or each managed device (al=
l other deployments).
                                                                     </p>
                                                                    =20
                                                                  </li>
                                                                  <li class=
=3D"li">
                                                                    =20
                                                                     <p cla=
ss=3D"p">If you use strong cryptographic functionality: </p>
                                                                    =20
                                                                     <ul cl=
ass=3D"ul">
                                                                        <li=
 class=3D"li">
                                                                          =
=20
                                                                           =
<p class=3D"p">If your entire Smart Account is enabled for export-controlle=
d functionality, you do not need to do anything here. </p>
                                                                          =
=20
                                                                        </l=
i>
                                                                        <li=
 class=3D"li">
                                                                          =
=20
                                                                           =
<p class=3D"p">If your organization's entitlement is per-Firepower Manageme=
nt Center, you must select the appropriate license for your appliance.
                                                                           =
  =20
                                                                           =
</p>
                                                                          =
=20
                                                                           =
<p class=3D"p">For the correct license name to choose for your device, see =
the prerequisites in <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/u=
s/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/l=
icensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_80874">Enabling the Export Control Fe=
ature (for Accounts Without Global Permission)</a>.
                                                                           =
</p>
                                                                          =
=20
                                                                        </l=
i>
                                                                     </ul>
                                                                    =20
                                                                  </li>
                                                               </ul>
                                                              =20
                                                            </section>
                                                         </td>
                                                      </tr>
                                                   </tbody></table></div>
                                                  =20
                                                </section>
                                             </li>
