                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <=
span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Next</span> and verify the details.
                                                </p>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <=
span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Generate Authorization Code</span>.
                                                </p>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Downloa=
d the Authorization Code in preparation for entering it into the Firepower =
Management Center.</p>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Leave t=
he Update Reservation page open. You will return to it later in this proced=
ure.</p>
                                             </li>
                                          </ol>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Update the Sp=
ecific Licenses in Firepower Management Center:</p>
                                          <ol type=3D"a" class=3D"ol subste=
ps">
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Choose =
<span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span></=
span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Lice=
nses</span></span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph ui=
control">Specific Licenses</span></span>.
                                                </p>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <=
span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Edit SLR</span>.
                                                </p>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <=
span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Browse</span> to upload the newly generated aut=
horization code.
                                                </p>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd"> Click =
<span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Install</span> to update the licenses.
                                                </p>
                                                <section class=3D"itemgroup=
 info">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">After suc=
cessful installation of the authorization code, ensure that the licenses sh=
own in the Reserved column of Firepower
                                                      Management Center, ma=
tches with the licenses that you have reserved in Cisco Smart Software Mana=
ger.=20
                                                   </p>
                                                  =20
                                                </section>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Make a =
note of the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Confirmation Code</span>.
                                                </p>
                                             </li>
                                          </ol>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;5</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Enter the con=
firmation code in Cisco Smart Software Manager:</p>
                                          <ol type=3D"a" class=3D"ol subste=
ps">
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Return =
to the Cisco Smart Software Manager page that you left open earlier in this=
 procedure.</p>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Choose =
<span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Actions</span><=
/span> &gt;<span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol"> Ent=
er Confirmation Code</span></span>:
                                                </p>
                                                <section class=3D"itemgroup=
 info">
                                                  =20
                                                   <figure class=3D"fig fig=
none"><a href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/42000=
1-430000/428001-429000/428838.jpg" class=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"Rela=
ted image, diagram or screenshot."><img class=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.=
cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/420001-430000/428001-429000/428838=
.jpg" width=3D"700"></a></figure>
                                                  =20
                                                </section>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Enter t=
he confirmation code that you generated from the Firepower Management Cente=
r.</p>
                                             </li>
                                          </ol>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;6</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">In Firepower =
Management Center, verify that your licenses are reserved as you expect the=
m, and that each feature for each
                                             managed device shows a green c=
ircle with a <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Check Mark</sp=
an>
                                                (<a href=3D"https://www.cis=
co.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/440001-450000/446001-447000/446558.jp=
g" class=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"check mark icon"><img class=3D"image=
" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/440001-450000=
/446001-447000/446558.jpg" alt=3D"check mark icon"></a>)</span>.
                                          </p>
                                          <section class=3D"itemgroup info"=
>
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">If necessary, s=
ee <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security=
/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firep=
ower_system.html#id_79535">Specific License Reservation Status</a> for more=
 information.
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                          </section>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                 </tbody>
                              </table></div>
                              <hr noshade=3D"">
                              <section class=3D"section postreq" id=3D"id_7=
9540__d262094e5884">
                                 <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                    <h5 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"secti=
ontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">What to do next</h5>
                                 </section>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">If your deployment includes=
 export-controlled functionality, reboot each device.  If devices are confi=
gured in a high-availability
                                    pair, reboot both devices at the same t=
ime to avoid an Active-Active condition.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_79540__deploy_conf=
ig_changes"><span class=3D"ph" id=3D"id_79540__ph_deploy_config_changes">De=
ploy configuration changes; see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco=
.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-=
guide-v70/policy_management.html#task_75E181687ECF4EFC8EB6AF4509C20C0B">Dep=
loy Configuration Changes</a>.</span>
                                   =20
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title45" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_87357">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le45">Important!  Maintain Your SLR Deployment</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_87357__d2=
62094e5909">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">To update the threat data a=
nd software that keep your deployment effective, see <a class=3D"xref" href=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configurati=
on/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/system_software_updates.html#id_87354">Maint=
ain Your Air-Gapped Deployment</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">To ensure that all function=
ality continues to work without interruption, monitor your license expirati=
on dates (on the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Reserved Licenses</span> tab)=
.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title46" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_79535">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le46">Specific License Reservation Status</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_79535__d2=
62094e5934">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Usage Aut=
horization</h5>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">The <span class=3D"ph uicon=
trol">System</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Licenses</span> &gt; =
<span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Specific Licenses</span> page provides an over=
view of license usage on the Firepower Management Center, as described belo=
w.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Possible status values are:=
</p>
                                =20
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b=
">Authorized</strong> =E2=80=94 The Firepower Management Center is in compl=
iance and registered successfully with the License Authority, which has aut=
horized
                                          the license entitlements for the =
appliance.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b=
">Out-of-compliance</strong> =E2=80=94 If licenses are expired or if the Fi=
repower Management Center has overused licenses even though they are not re=
served,
                                          status shows as Out-of-Compliance=
. License entitlements are enforced in Specific License Reservation, so you=
 must take action.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                 </ul>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_79535__d2=
62094e5970">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Product R=
egistration</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Specifies registration stat=
us and the date that an authorization code was last installed or renewed on=
 the Firepower Management
                                    Center.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_79535__d2=
62094e5978">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Export-Co=
ntrolled Features</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Specifies whether you have =
enabled export-controlled functionality for the Firepower Management Center=
.</p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">For more information about =
Export-Controlled Features, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco=
.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-=
guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_81552">Licensing for Expor=
t-Controlled Functionality</a>.=20
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_79535__d2=
62094e5993">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Product I=
nstance</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">The Universally Unique Iden=
tifier (UUID) of this Firepower Management Center. This value identifies th=
is device in Cisco Smart
                                    Software Manager.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_79535__d2=
62094e6001">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Confirmat=
ion Code</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">The <span class=3D"ph uicon=
trol">Confirmation Code</span> is needed if you update or deactivate and re=
turn Specific Licenses.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_79535__d2=
62094e6012">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Assigned =
Licenses Tab</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Shows the licenses assigned=
 to each device and the status of each.</p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_79535__d2=
62094e6020">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Reserved =
Licenses Tab</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Shows the number of license=
s used and available to be assigned, and license expiration dates.</p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic concept nested3" aria-label=
ledby=3D"ariaid-title47" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_90603">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le47">Expired Specific License Reservation</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body conbody">
                              <p class=3D"p">If required licenses are unava=
ilable or expired, the following actions are restricted:</p>
                              <ul class=3D"ul">
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Device registration</p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Policy deployment</p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                              </ul>
                              <p class=3D"p">To renew your Specific License=
 Reservation entitlements, purchase the necessary licenses, then follow the=
 procedure in <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/do=
cs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensin=
g_the_firepower_system.html#id_79540">Update a Specific License Reservation=
</a>.
                              </p>
                           </section>
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title48" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_92463">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le48">Renew Specific License Reservation Entitlements</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_92463__d2=
62094e6067">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">When it is time to renew yo=
ur Specific License Reservation entitlements, purchase the necessary licens=
es, then follow the
                                    procedure in <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"=
https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/g=
uide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_79540">Up=
date a Specific License Reservation</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic task nested3 no_summary_ste=
ps" aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title49" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_79541">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le49">Deactivate and Return the Specific License Reservation</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                              <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"id_7=
9541__d262094e6086">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">If you no longer need a spe=
cific license, you must return it to your Smart Account.</p>
                                =20
                                 <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=
=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                    <tbody><tr>
                                       <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" =
role=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam=
/en/us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Important</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                          <section class=3D"note__content">
                                             <hr>
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">If you do not f=
ollow all of the steps in this procedure, the license remains in
                                                an in-use state and cannot =
be re-used.
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                             <hr>
                                          </section>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                 </tbody></table></div>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">This procedure releases all=
 license entitlements associated with the Firepower Management Center back =
to your virtual account.
                                    After you de-register, no updates or ch=
anges on licensed features are allowed.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                 <h5 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiont=
itle tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h5>
                              </section>
                              <hr noshade=3D"">
                              <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D=
"stepTable" border=3D"0">
                                 <tbody>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">In the Firepo=
wer Management Center Web interface, select <span class=3D"ph menucascade">=
<span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span></span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph me=
nucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Licenses</span></span> &gt;<span cl=
ass=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol"> Specific Licenses</spa=
n></span>.=20
                                          </p>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Make a note o=
f the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Product Instance</span> identifier for t=
his <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span=
></span>.
                                          </p>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Generate a re=
turn code from Firepower Management Center:</p>
                                          <ol type=3D"a" class=3D"ol subste=
ps">
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <=
span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Return SLR</span>.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <section class=3D"itemgroup=
 info">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">The follo=
wing figure shows Return SLR.</p>
                                                  =20
                                                   <figure class=3D"fig fig=
none">
                                                      <a href=3D"https://ww=
w.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/420001-430000/428001-429000/4288=
39.jpg" class=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"Related image, diagram or scree=
nshot."><img class=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/=
400001-500000/420001-430000/428001-429000/428839.jpg" width=3D"700"></a>
                                                     =20
                                                   </figure>
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Firepower=
 Threat Defense devices become unlicensed and Firepower Management Center m=
oves to the de-registered state.</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </section>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Make a =
note of the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Return Code</span>.
                                                </p>
                                             </li>
                                          </ol>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">In Cisco Smar=
t Software Manager, identify the Firepower Management Center appliance to d=
eregister:</p>
                                          <ol type=3D"a" class=3D"ol subste=
ps">
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Go to t=
he Cisco Smart Software Manager: </p>
                                                <section class=3D"itemgroup=
 info">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p"><a class=
=3D"xref" href=3D"https://software.cisco.com/#SmartLicensing-Inventory" tar=
get=3D"_blank">https://software.cisco.com/#SmartLicensing-Inventory</a></p>
                                                  =20
                                                </section>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">If nece=
ssary, click <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Inventory</span>.
                                                </p>
                                                <section class=3D"itemgroup=
 info">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">(This pag=
e may display automatically.)</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </section>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <=
span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Product Instances</span>.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Look fo=
r a product instance that has <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">FP</span> in the=
 <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Type</span> column and a generic SKU (not a h=
ostname) in the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Name</span> column. You may al=
so be able to use the values in other table columns to help determine which=
 Firepower Management Center
                                                   is the correct Firepower=
 Management Center. Click the name.
                                                </p>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Look at=
 the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">UUID</span> and see if it is the UUID of =
the Firepower Management Center that you are trying to modify.
                                                </p>
                                                <section class=3D"itemgroup=
 info">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">If not, y=
ou must repeat these steps until you find the correct Firepower Management =
Center.</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </section>
                                             </li>
                                          </ol>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;5</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">When you have=
 identified the correct Firepower Management Center, return the licenses to=
 your Smart Account:</p>
                                          <ol type=3D"a" class=3D"ol subste=
ps">
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">On the =
page that shows the correct UUID, choose <span class=3D"ph menucascade"><sp=
an class=3D"ph uicontrol">Actions</span></span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph menu=
cascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Remove</span></span>.=20
                                                </p>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Enter t=
he reservation return code that you generated from the Firepower Management=
 Center into the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Remove Product Instance</span=
> dialog box.=20
                                                </p>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <=
span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Remove Product Instance</span>.
                                                </p>
                                                <section class=3D"itemgroup=
 info">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">The speci=
fic reserved licenses are returned to the available pool in your Smart Acco=
unt and this Firepower Management Center
                                                      is removed from the C=
isco Smart Software Manager Product Instances list.
                                                   </p>
                                                  =20
                                                </section>
                                             </li>
                                          </ol>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr class=3D"li step">
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                          <p><b>Step&nbsp;6</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" bo=
rder=3D"0">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Disable the S=
pecific License in the Firepower Management Center Linux shell:</p>
                                          <ol type=3D"a" class=3D"ol subste=
ps">
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Access =
the Firepower Management Center console using a USB keyboard and VGA monito=
r, or use SSH to access the management interface.</p>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Log in =
to the Firepower Management Center <strong class=3D"ph b">admin</strong> ac=
count. <span class=3D"ph">This give you
                                                      access to the Firepow=
er Management Center CLI.</span>.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd"><span c=
lass=3D"ph">Enter  the
                                                      <span><span class=3D"=
keyword kwd">expert</span> </span> command to access the Linux
                                                      shell.</span></p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd" id=3D"i=
d_79541__disableslr">Execute the following command:</p>
                                                <section class=3D"itemgroup=
 info">
                                                  =20
                                                   <section class=3D"p">
                                                      <pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>sudo manage_slr.pl</code></pre>
                                                      </section>
                                                  =20
                                                </section>
                                                <section class=3D"itemgroup=
 stepxmp">
                                                   <section class=3D"taskla=
bel">
                                                      <h5 font-weight=3D"bo=
ld" class=3D"sectiontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">Example:</h5>
                                                   </section>
                                                   <pre class=3D"pre codebl=
ock"><code>admin@fmc63betaslr: ~$ sudo manage_slr.pl
Password:


**************** Configuration Utility **************

1   Show SLR Status
2   Enable SLR
3   Disable SLR
0   Exit

**************************************************************
Enter choice:
</code></pre>
                                                   </section>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Select =
menu option 3 to disable the Specific License Reservation.</p>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Select =
option 0 to exit the manage_slr utility.</p>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd">Enter <=
span><span class=3D"keyword kwd">exit</span> </span> to exit the Linux shel=
l.
                                                </p>
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li substep subste=
pexpand">
                                                <p class=3D"ph cmd"><span c=
lass=3D"ph">Enter</span>
                                                   <span><span class=3D"key=
word kwd">exit</span> </span> to exit the command line interface.
                                                </p>
                                             </li>
                                          </ol>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                 </tbody>
                              </table></div>
                              <hr noshade=3D"">
                           </section>
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title50" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_84365">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le50">Troubleshoot Specific License Reservation</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_84365__d2=
62094e6320">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">How do I =
identify a particular Firepower Management Center in the Product Instance l=
ist in Cisco Smart Software Manager? </h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">On the Product Instances pa=
ge in Cisco Smart Software Manager, if you cannot identify the product inst=
ance based on a value
                                    in one of the columns in the table, you=
 must click the name of each generic product instance of type <span class=
=3D"ph uicontrol">FP</span> to view the product instance details page. The =
<span class=3D"ph uicontrol">UUID</span> value on this page uniquely identi=
fies one Firepower Management Center.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">In the Firepower Management=
 Center web interface, the UUID for a Firepower Management Center is the <s=
pan class=3D"ph uicontrol">Product Instance</span> value displayed on the <=
span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System &gt; Licenses &gt; Specific Licenses</sp=
an> page.=20
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_84365__d2=
62094e6343">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">I do not =
see a License Reservation button in Cisco Smart Software Manager</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">If you do not see the <span=
 class=3D"ph uicontrol">License Reservation</span> button, then your accoun=
t is not authorized for specific license reservation. If you have already e=
nabled Specific License
                                    Reservation in the Linux shell and gene=
rated a request code, perform the following:
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <ol class=3D"ol">
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">If you have already g=
enerated a <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Request Code</span> in the Firepowe=
r Management Center web interface, cancel the request code.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Disable Specific Lice=
nse Reservation in the Firepower Management Center Linux shell as described=
 within the section  <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/u=
s/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/l=
icensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_79541">Deactivate and Return the Spec=
ific License Reservation</a>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Register a Firepower =
Management Center with Cisco Smart Software Manager in regular mode using s=
mart token. </p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Contact Cisco TAC to =
enable Specific License for your smart account. </p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                 </ol>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_84365__d2=
62094e6383">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">I was int=
errupted in the middle of the licensing process. How can I pick up where I =
left off?</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">If you have generated but n=
ot yet downloaded an Authorization code from Cisco Smart Software Manager, =
you can go to the<span class=3D"keyword wintitle"> Product Instance</span> =
page in Cisco Smart Software Manager, click the product instance, then clic=
k <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Download Reservation Authorization Code</spa=
n>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_84365__d2=
62094e6397">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">I am unab=
le to register Firepower Threat Defense devices to Firepower Management Cen=
ter Virtual</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Make sure you have enough M=
Cv entitlements in your Smart Account to cover the devices you want to regi=
ster, then update your
                                    deployment to add the necessary entitle=
ments.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">See  <a class=3D"xref" href=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configurati=
on/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_79540=
">Update a Specific License Reservation</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_84365__d2=
62094e6412">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">I have en=
abled Specific Licensing, but now I do not see a Smart License page. </h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">This is the expected behavi=
or. When you enable Specific Licensing, Smart Licensing is disabled. You ca=
n use the Specific License
                                    page to perform licensing operations.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">If you want to use Smart Li=
censing, you must return the Specific License. For more information see, <a=
 class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/fire=
power/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_=
system.html#id_79541">Deactivate and Return the Specific License Reservatio=
n</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_84365__d2=
62094e6427">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">What if I=
 do not see a Specific License page in Firepower Management Center?</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">You need to enable Specific=
 License to view the Specific License page. For more information see, <a cl=
ass=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepow=
er/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_sys=
tem.html#id_79537">Enable the Specific Licensing Menu Option</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_84365__d2=
62094e6439">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">I have di=
sabled Specific Licensing, but forgot to copy the Return Code. What should =
I do?</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">The <span class=3D"ph uicon=
trol">Return Code</span> is saved in Firepower Management Center. You must =
re-enable the Specific License from the Linux shell (see <a class=3D"xref" =
href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configu=
ration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_7=
9537">Enable the Specific Licensing Menu Option</a>), then refresh the Fire=
power Management Center web interface. Your <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Re=
turn Code</span> will be displayed.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                        </article>
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic task nested2 no_summary_steps"=
 aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title51" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_75162">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title5=
1">Assign Licenses to Multiple Managed Devices</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                           <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"id_7516=
2__d262094e6493">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Devices managed by a <span cla=
ss=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> obta=
in their licenses via the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower M=
anagement Center</span></span>, not directly from the Cisco Smart Software =
Manager.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Use this procedure to enable l=
icensing on multiple <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat=
 Defense</span></span> devices at once.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D=
"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                 <tbody><tr>
                                    <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" rol=
e=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en=
/us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                       <section class=3D"note__content">
                                          <hr>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">For container inst=
ances on the same <span class=3D"ph">security module/engine</span>, you app=
ly the license to each instance; note that the <span class=3D"ph">security =
module/engine</span> consumes only one license per feature for all instance=
s on the <span class=3D"ph">security module/engine</span>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <hr>
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody></table></div>
                             =20
                              <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D=
"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                 <tbody><tr>
                                    <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" rol=
e=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en=
/us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                       <section class=3D"note__content">
                                          <hr>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">For an <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> cluster, =
you apply the licenses to the cluster as a whole; note that each unit in th=
e cluster consumes a separate license
                                             per feature.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <hr>
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody></table></div>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"section prereq p" id=3D"id_751=
62__d262094e6468">
                              <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                 <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiont=
itle tasklabel cB_Bold">Before you begin</h4>
                              </section>
                             =20
                              <ul class=3D"ul">
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">If you have not yet done=
 so, register your devices with the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">F=
irepower Management Center</span></span>. See <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"htt=
ps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guid=
e/fpmc-config-guide-v70/device_management_basics.html#ID-2242-0000069d">Add=
 a Device to the FMC</a>.
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Prepare licenses for dis=
tribution to managed devices: See <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cis=
co.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-confi=
g-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#task_E14666F0D32E45FE820B52=
C9D3103B6F">Register Smart Licenses</a></p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                              </ul>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h4>
                           </section>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"st=
epTable" border=3D"0">
                              <tbody>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"id_75162__step=
_C49A3FACB53042EFBD491854F7D6EE40">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Choose <span cla=
ss=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Syste=
m</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Licenses</span> &gt; <span class=
=3D"ph uicontrol">Smart Licenses</span></span></span><span class=3D"ph"> or=
 <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Specific Licenses</span></span>.=20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <span clas=
s=3D"ph uicontrol">Edit Licenses</span>.
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">For each type of=
 license you want to add to a device: </p>
                                       <ol type=3D"a" class=3D"ol substeps"=
>
                                          <li class=3D"li substep substepex=
pand">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click the =
tab for that type of license.</p>
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li substep substepex=
pand">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click a de=
vice in the list on the left.</p>
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li substep substepex=
pand">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <spa=
n class=3D"ph uicontrol">Add</span> to move that device to the list on the =
right.
                                             </p>
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li substep substepex=
pand">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">Repeat for=
 each device to receive that type of license.</p>
                                             <section class=3D"itemgroup in=
fo">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">For now, don=
't worry about whether you have licenses for all of the devices you want to=
 add.</p>
                                               =20
                                             </section>
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li substep substepex=
pand">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">Repeat thi=
s subprocedure for each type of license you want to add.</p>
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li substep substepex=
pand">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <spa=
n class=3D"ph uicontrol">Apply</span>.
                                             </p>
                                          </li>
                                       </ol>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <section class=3D"section postreq" id=3D"id_7516=
2__d262094e6594">
                              <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                 <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiont=
itle tasklabel cB_Bold">What to do next</h4>
                              </section>
                             =20
                              <ul class=3D"ul">
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Verify that your license=
s are correctly installed. Follow the procedure in <a class=3D"xref" href=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configurati=
on/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#task_E06=
E766894744E2B81D476F727569502">View FTD Licenses and License Status</a>.
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">If export-controlled fun=
ctionality is newly enabled, reboot each device.  If devices are configured=
 in a high-availability
                                       pair, reboot both devices at the sam=
e time to avoid an Active-Active condition.
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                 <li class=3D"li" id=3D"id_75162__li_EC4768=
457A7544F4B51493E23CB346AA">
                                    									=09
                                    <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph">Deplo=
y configuration changes; see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.co=
m/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-gui=
de-v70/policy_management.html#task_75E181687ECF4EFC8EB6AF4509C20C0B">Deploy=
 Configuration Changes</a>.</span></p>
                                    								=09
                                 </li>
                              </ul>
                             =20
                           </section>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic task nested2 no_summary_steps"=
 aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title52" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"task_E06E766894744=
E2B81D476F727569502">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title5=
2">View FTD Licenses and License Status</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                           <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"task_E0=
6E766894744E2B81D476F727569502__context_FDAE08BDC2ED492FA36DFB30884864A2">
                              		=09
                              <p class=3D"p">To view the license status for=
 a <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span>=
</span> and its managed <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Thr=
eat Defense</span></span> devices, use the Smart Licenses page in FMC.
                              </p>
                              		=09
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"task_E06E766894744E2B81D=
476F727569502__ID-2240-000002c6">For each type of license in your deploymen=
t, the page lists the total number of licenses consumed, whether the licens=
e is
                                 in compliance or out of compliance, the de=
vice type, and the domain and group where the device is deployed. You can a=
lso view
                                 the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">=
Firepower Management Center</span></span>'s Smart License Status.<span clas=
s=3D"ph"> Container instances on the same <span class=3D"ph">security modul=
e/engine</span> only consume one license per <span class=3D"ph">security mo=
dule/engine</span>. Therefore, even though the <span class=3D"ph"><span cla=
ss=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> lists each container instance separately under =
each license type, the number of licenses consumed for feature license type=
s
                                    will only be one.</span></p>
                              		=09
                              		=09
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"task_E06E766894744E2B81D=
476F727569502__ID-2240-000002cc">Other than the Smart Licenses page, there =
are a few other ways you can view licenses: </p>
                              		=09
                              <ul class=3D"ul">
                                 <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_E06E766894744E=
2B81D476F727569502__li_ECF1AB333F0F4AF9A98A8889429B5C33">
                                    				=09
                                    <p class=3D"p" id=3D"task_E06E766894744=
E2B81D476F727569502__ID-2240-000002cd">The Product Licensing dashboard widg=
et provides an at-a-glance overview of your licenses. </p>
                                    				=09
                                    <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xref" hr=
ef=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configura=
tion/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/dashboards.html#ID-2206-00000ac4">Adding W=
idgets to a Dashboard</a> and <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.c=
om/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-gu=
ide-v70/dashboards.html#ID-2206-0000015a">Dashboard Widget Availability by =
User Role</a> and  <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/=
td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/das=
hboards.html#ID-2206-00000936">The Product Licensing Widget</a>.
                                    </p>
                                    			=09
                                 </li>
                                 <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_E06E766894744E=
2B81D476F727569502__li_B52B4C73A9084C83BFB2C7F04BAA7769">
                                    				=09
                                    <p class=3D"p" id=3D"task_E06E766894744=
E2B81D476F727569502__ID-2240-000002cf">The Device Management page (<span cl=
ass=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Devi=
ces</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Device Management</span></span=
></span>) lists the licenses applied to each of your managed devices.=20
                                    </p>
                                    			=09
                                 </li>
                                 <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_E06E766894744E=
2B81D476F727569502__li_3F60DE1BD8CD4A3599393B5538A95DE2">
                                    				=09
                                    <p class=3D"p" id=3D"task_E06E766894744=
E2B81D476F727569502__ID-2240-000002d2">The Smart License Monitor health mod=
ule communicates license status when used in a health policy. </p>
                                    			=09
                                 </li>
                              </ul>
                              	=09
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h4>
                           </section>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"st=
epTable" border=3D"0">
                              <tbody>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"task_E06E76689=
4744E2B81D476F727569502__step_C1A423B176D2442E81D08AA0EE5449BA">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Choose <span cla=
ss=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Syste=
m</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Licenses</span> &gt; <span class=
=3D"ph uicontrol">Smart Licenses</span></span></span>.=20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">In the <span cla=
ss=3D"ph uicontrol">Smart Licenses</span> table, click the arrow at the lef=
t side of each <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">License Type</span> folder to e=
xpand that folder.
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">In each folder, =
verify that each device has a green circle with a <span class=3D"ph"><span =
class=3D"ph uicontrol">Check Mark</span>
                                             (<a href=3D"https://www.cisco.=
com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/440001-450000/446001-447000/446558.jpg" =
class=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"check mark icon"><img class=3D"image" s=
rc=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/440001-450000/44=
6001-447000/446558.jpg" alt=3D"check mark icon"></a>)</span> in the <span c=
lass=3D"ph uicontrol">License Status</span> column.=20
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                          				=09
                                          <div class=3D"tableContainer"><ta=
ble class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                             <tbody><tr>
                                                <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"t=
d_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                   <p><b>Note</b></p>&nbsp;
                                                </td>
                                                <td border=3D"0" class=3D"t=
d_faq">
                                                   <section class=3D"note__=
content">
                                                      					=09
                                                      <p class=3D"p">If you=
 see duplicate <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management C=
enter</span></span> Virtual licenses, each represents one managed device.
                                                      </p>
                                                      				=09
                                                   </section>
                                                </td>
                                             </tr>
                                          </tbody></table></div>
                                          				=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">If all devices sho=
w a green circle with a <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Che=
ck Mark</span>
                                                (<a href=3D"https://www.cis=
co.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/440001-450000/446001-447000/446558.jp=
g" class=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"check mark icon"><img class=3D"image=
" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/440001-450000=
/446001-447000/446558.jpg" alt=3D"check mark icon"></a>)</span>, your devic=
es are properly licensed and ready to use.
                                          </p>
                                          				=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">If you see any Lic=
ense Status other than a green circle with a <span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph uicontrol">Check Mark</span>
                                                (<a href=3D"https://www.cis=
co.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/440001-450000/446001-447000/446558.jp=
g" class=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"check mark icon"><img class=3D"image=
" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/440001-450000=
/446001-447000/446558.jpg" alt=3D"check mark icon"></a>)</span>, hover over=
 the status icon to view the message.=20
                                          </p>
                                          			=09
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <section class=3D"section postreq" id=3D"task_E0=
6E766894744E2B81D476F727569502__d262094e6810">
                              <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                 <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiont=
itle tasklabel cB_Bold">What to do next</h4>
                              </section>
                              		=09
                              <ul class=3D"ul">
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                    				=09
                                    <p class=3D"p">If you had any devices t=
hat did NOT have a green circle with a <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph=
 uicontrol">Check Mark</span>
                                          (<a href=3D"https://www.cisco.com=
/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/440001-450000/446001-447000/446558.jpg" cla=
ss=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"check mark icon"><img class=3D"image" src=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/440001-450000/4460=
01-447000/446558.jpg" alt=3D"check mark icon"></a>)</span>, you may need to=
 purchase more licenses.
                                    </p>
                                    			=09
                                 </li>
                              </ul>
                              	=09
                           </section>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links">
                           <ul class=3D"ullinks">
                              <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guid=
e/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#reference_F1702=
7F025874ABB8199973C3997FC30">FTD License Status</a></li>
                           </ul>
                        </nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title53" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"reference_F17027F025874ABB8=
199973C3997FC30">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le53">FTD License Status</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              	=09
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_F1=
7027F025874ABB8199973C3997FC30__d262094e6869">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Permanent=
 License Reservation</h5>
                                 		=09
                                 		=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xref" href=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configurati=
on/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_79535=
">Specific License Reservation Status</a></p>
                                 	=09
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_F1=
7027F025874ABB8199973C3997FC30__section_D95CCB443559402E9B89BDF4E61775CC">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Smart Lic=
ensing</h5>
                                 			=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">The Smart License Status se=
ction of the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System &gt; Licenses &gt; Smart L=
icenses</span> page provides an overview of license usage on the <span clas=
s=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>, as d=
escribed below.=20
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_F1=
7027F025874ABB8199973C3997FC30__section_CCA1AC1AC79C45B3827077564AB2FF03">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Usage
                                    		  Authorization
                                 </h5>=20
                                 		=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">Possible status values are:=
 </p>
                                 		=09
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph"><s=
pan class=3D"ph uicontrol">In-compliance</span> (<a href=3D"https://www.cis=
co.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/440001-450000/448001-449000/448268.jp=
g" class=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"in-compliance icon"><img class=3D"im=
age" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/440001-450=
000/448001-449000/448268.jpg" alt=3D"in-compliance icon"></a>)</span> =E2=
=80=94 All licenses assigned to managed devices are in compliance and the <=
span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></sp=
an> is communicating successfully with the Cisco licensing authority.
                                       </p>
                                       			=09
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph uic=
ontrol">License is in compliance but communication with licensing authority=
 has failed</span>=E2=80=94 Device licenses are in compliance, but the <spa=
n class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>=
 is not able to communicate with the Cisco licensing authority.=20
                                       </p>
                                       			=09
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
