                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph uic=
ontrol">Out-of-compliance icon or unable to communicate with License Author=
ity</span>=E2=80=94 One or more managed devices is using a license that is =
out of compliance, or the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower M=
anagement Center</span></span> has not communicated with the Cisco licensin=
g authority in more than 90 days.
                                       </p>
                                       			=09
                                    </li>
                                 </ul>=20
                                 		=20
                                 	=20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_F1=
7027F025874ABB8199973C3997FC30__section_7B160117D8364923BCA231B798E8B883">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Product
                                    		  Registration
                                 </h5>=20
                                 		=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">Specifies the last
                                    		  date when the=20
                                    		  <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"p=
h">Firepower Management Center</span></span>
                                    		  contacted the License Authority and=
 registered.=20
                                    	=09
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_F1=
7027F025874ABB8199973C3997FC30__section_B556C6DDA05741E285D85D798B42F421">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Assigned =
Virtual
                                    		  Account
                                 </h5>=20
                                 		=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">Specifies the Virtual Accou=
nt under the Smart Account that you used to generate the Product Instance R=
egistration Token and
                                    register the <span class=3D"ph"><span c=
lass=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>. If this deployment i=
s not associated with a particular virtual account within your Smart Accoun=
t, this information is not
                                    displayed.
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_F1=
7027F025874ABB8199973C3997FC30__section_FEA6CA068474487E8F34DFBD9CF0426B">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Export-Co=
ntrolled Features</h5>
                                 		=09
                                 		=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">If this option is enabled, =
you can deploy restricted features.  For details, see <a class=3D"xref" hre=
f=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configurat=
ion/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_8155=
2">Licensing for Export-Controlled Functionality</a>.
                                 </p>
                                 	=09
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_F1=
7027F025874ABB8199973C3997FC30__d262094e6982">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Cisco Suc=
cess Network</h5>
                                 		=09
                                 		=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">Specifies whether you have =
enabled Cisco Success Network for the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph"=
>Firepower Management Center</span></span>. If this option is enabled, you =
provide usage information and statistics to Cisco which are essential to pr=
ovide you with
                                    technical support. This information als=
o allows Cisco to improve the product and make you aware of unused availabl=
e features
                                    so that you can maximize the value of t=
he product in your network. See <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco=
.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-=
guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_60544">Cisco Success Netwo=
rk</a> for more information.
                                 </p>
                                 	=09
                              </section>
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic task nested2 no_summary_steps"=
 aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title54" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"task_2386ECC9E89C4=
D2B940881F1D39ECA45">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title5=
4">Move or Remove Licenses from FTD Devices</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                           <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"task_23=
86ECC9E89C4D2B940881F1D39ECA45__context_753CB0AC2C06454199B382839DE586EE">=
=20
                              	=09
                              <p class=3D"p">Use this procedure to manage l=
icenses for <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense<=
/span></span> devices managed by an <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">F=
irepower Management Center</span></span>.
                              </p>
                              		=09
                              <p class=3D"p">For example, you can move a li=
cense from one FTD device to another device registered to the same FMC, or =
to remove a license
                                 from a device.=20
                              </p>
                              		=09
                              <p class=3D"p">If you remove (disable) a lice=
nse for a device, you cannot use the features associated with that license =
on that device.</p>
                              		=09
                              <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D=
"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                 <tbody><tr>
                                    <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" rol=
e=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en=
/us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Important</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                       <section class=3D"note__content">
                                          <hr>
                                          			=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">If you need to mov=
e a license to a device managed by a <em class=3D"ph i">different</em>
                                             					<span class=3D"ph"><span =
class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>, see <a class=3D"xre=
f" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/conf=
iguration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#c=

                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title55" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"concept_5DB3F9F2A08449F7A38FCF8C=
06516520">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title5=
5">Transfer FTD Licenses to a Different <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"p=
h">Firepower Management Center</span></span></h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <p class=3D"p">When you register a Smart License=
 to a <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</sp=
an></span>, your virtual account allocates the license to the <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>. If you need to transfer your =
Smart Licenses to another <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower M=
anagement Center</span></span>, you must deregister the currently licensed =
<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>. This removes it fr=
om your virtual account and frees your existing licenses, so you can regist=
er the licenses to the new
                              <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</sp=
an></span>. Otherwise, you cannot reuse these licenses, and you may receive=
 an Out-of-Compliance notification because your virtual account
                              does not have enough free licenses. For instr=
uctions, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/doc=
s/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing=
_the_firepower_system.html#task_E9C821FFDC2A4958A3A5F536E89EB895">Deregiste=
r a Firepower Management Center from the Cisco Smart Software Manager</a>.
                           </p>
                           <p class=3D"p">Then you can register the license=
s to the destination <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Manage=
ment Center</span></span>.
                           </p>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic task nested2 no_summary_steps"=
 aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title56" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_85795">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title5=
6">If FTD License Status is Out of Compliance</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                           <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"id_8579=
5__d262094e7241">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">If the Usage Authorization sta=
tus on the Smart Licenses page (<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph menuca=
scade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph ui=
control">Licenses</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Smart Licenses</=
span></span></span>) shows Out of Compliance, you must take action.
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h4>
                           </section>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"st=
epTable" border=3D"0">
                              <tbody>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Look at the Smar=
t Licenses section at the bottom of the page to determine which licenses ar=
e needed. </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Purchase the req=
uired licenses through your usual channels.</p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">In Cisco Smart S=
oftware Manager (<a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://software.cisco.com/#Smar=
tLicensing-Inventory" target=3D"_blank">https://software.cisco.com/#SmartLi=
censing-Inventory</a>), verify that the licenses appear in your virtual acc=
ount.
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">If the expected li=
censes are not present, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com=
/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guid=
e-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_85339">Troubleshoot FTD Licens=
ing</a>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">In <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>, selec=
t <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicon=
trol">System</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Licenses</span> &gt; =
<span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Smart Licenses</span></span></span>. =20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;5</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <span clas=
s=3D"ph uicontrol">Re-Authorize</span>.
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic task nested2 no_summary_steps"=
 aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title57" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"task_E9C821FFDC2A4=
958A3A5F536E89EB895">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title5=
7">Deregister a <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management =
Center</span></span> from the Cisco Smart Software Manager
                        </h3>
                        <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                           <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"task_E9=
C821FFDC2A4958A3A5F536E89EB895__context_E9ACC485760140B5B3E4912371827440">
                              		=09
                              <p class=3D"p">Deregister (unregister) your <=
span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></sp=
an> from the Cisco Smart Software Manager before you reinstall (reimage) th=
e appliance, or if you need to release all of the
                                 license entitlements back to your Smart Ac=
count for any reason.
                              </p>=20
                              	=09
                              <p class=3D"p">Deregistering removes the <spa=
n class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> from your virtual accou=
nt. All license entitlements associated with the <span class=3D"ph"><span c=
lass=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> release back to your =
virtual account. After deregistration, the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> enters Enforcement mode w=
here no update or changes on licensed features are allowed.=20
                              </p>
                              		=09
                              <p class=3D"p">If you need to remove the lice=
nses from a subset of managed Firepower Threat Defense devices, see <a clas=
s=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower=
/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_syste=
m.html#id_75162">Assign Licenses to Multiple Managed Devices</a> or <a clas=
s=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower=
/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_syste=
m.html#ID-2240-00000342">Assign Licenses to Managed Devices from the Device=
 Management Page</a>.=20
                              </p>=20
                              	=20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h4>
                           </section>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"st=
epTable" border=3D"0">
                              <tbody>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"task_E9C821FFD=
C2A4958A3A5F536E89EB895__step_C49A3FACB53042EFBD491854F7D6EE40">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Choose <span cla=
ss=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Syste=
m</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Licenses</span> &gt; <span class=
=3D"ph uicontrol">Smart Licenses</span></span></span>.=20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"task_E9C821FFD=
C2A4958A3A5F536E89EB895__step_0974D832BBC145DA8725B90A957F18B7">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <span clas=
s=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Deregister</span>
                                             (<a href=3D"https://www.cisco.=
com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/440001-450000/448001-449000/448055.jpg" =
class=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"deregister icon"><img class=3D"image" s=
rc=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/440001-450000/44=
8001-449000/448055.jpg" alt=3D"deregister icon"></a>)</span>.=20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                        </section>

nav>

                     </article>

edby=3D"ariaid-title59" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_85339">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title5=
9">Troubleshoot FTD Licensing</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body refbody">
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_85339__d2620=
94e7503">
                              <h4 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Expected Lic=
enses Do Not Appear in My Smart Account</h4>
                             =20
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">If the licenses you expect to =
see are not in your Smart Account, try the following:</p>
                             =20
                              <ul class=3D"ul">
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Make sure they are not i=
n a different Virtual Account.  Your organization's license administrator m=
ay need to assist you with
                                       this.
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Check with the person wh=
o sold you the licenses to be sure that transfer to your account is complet=
e.</p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                              </ul>
                             =20
                           </section>
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_85339__d2620=
94e7524">
                              <h4 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Unable to Co=
nnect to Smart License Server</h4>
                             =20
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Check the obvious causes first=
.  For example, make sure your Firepower system has outside connectivity. S=
ee <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security=
/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/security_internet_a=
ccess_and_communication_ports.html#id_70300">Internet Access Requirements</=
a>.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_85339__d2620=
94e7536">
                              <h4 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Unexpected O=
ut-of-Compliance Notification or Other Error</h4>
                             =20
                             =20
                              <ul class=3D"ul">
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">If a device is already r=
egistered to a different FMC, you need to deregister the original FMC befor=
e you can license the device
                                       under a new FMC.  See  <a class=3D"x=
ref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/co=
nfiguration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html=
#task_E9C821FFDC2A4958A3A5F536E89EB895">Deregister a Firepower Management C=
enter from the Cisco Smart Software Manager</a>.=20
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Try synchronizing: <a cl=
ass=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepow=
er/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_sys=
tem.html#task_C0221C9135A2408C984856E928FD546F">Synchronize a Firepower Man=
agement Center with the Cisco Smart Software Manager</a>.
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>

FTDv Licensing</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body refbody">

                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"Cisco_Reference.di=
ta_6f768dd8-a296-4fd5-9d8f-3a26e1b543e2__d262094e7611">
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">This section describes the perfor=
mance-tiered license entitlements available for the <span class=3D"ph"><spa=
n class=3D"ph">FTDv</span></span>.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Any <span class=3D"ph"><span clas=
s=3D"ph">FTDv</span></span> license can be used on any supported <span clas=
s=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FTDv</span></span> vCPU/memory configuration. T=
his allows <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FTDv</span></span> custome=
rs to run on a wide variety of VM resource footprints. This also increases =
the number of supported AWS and Azure instances
                              types. When configuring the <span class=3D"ph=
"><span class=3D"ph">FTDv</span></span> VM, the maximum supported number of=
 cores (vCPUs) is 16 ; and the maximum supported memory is 32 GB RAM .
                           </p>
                          =20
                        </section>

lowing table summarizes the session limits based on the

                     <article class=3D"topic reference nested2" aria-labell=
edby=3D"ariaid-title61" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"Cisco_Reference.dita_4f8e93bb-=
a74e-40bf-ac87-f86208a86ac1">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title6=
1">FTDv Performance Tier Licensing Guidelines and Limitations</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body refbody">
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"Cisco_Reference=
.dita_4f8e93bb-a74e-40bf-ac87-f86208a86ac1__d262094e7908">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Please keep the following guid=
elines and limitations in mind when licensing your <span class=3D"ph"><span=
 class=3D"ph">FTDv</span></span> device.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <ul class=3D"ul">
                                =20
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">The <span class=3D"ph"><=
span class=3D"ph">FTDv</span></span> supports performance-tiered licensing =
that provides different throughput levels and VPN connection limits based o=
n deployment
                                       requirements.
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                =20
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Any <span class=3D"ph"><=
span class=3D"ph">FTDv</span></span> license can be used on any supported <=
span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FTDv</span></span> core/memory configu=
ration. This allows the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FTDv</span></=
span> customers to run on a wide variety of VM resource footprints.
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                =20
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">You can select a perform=
ance tier when you deploy the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FTDv</s=
pan></span>, whether your device is in evaluation mode or is already regist=
ered with <span class=3D"ph">Cisco Smart Software Manager</span>.=20
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                    <table class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" =
role=3D"note">
                                       <tbody><tr>
                                          <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_not=
e" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/=
dam/en/us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                          </td>
                                          <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_not=
e">
                                             <section class=3D"note__conten=
t">
                                                <hr>
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">Make sure yo=
ur Smart Licensing account contains the available licenses you need. It=E2=
=80=99s important to choose the tier that matches
                                                   the license you have in =
your account. If you are upgrading your <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"p=
h">FTDv</span></span> to Version 7.0, you can choose <span class=3D"ph uico=
ntrol">FTDv - Variable</span> to maintain your current license compliance. =
Your <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FTDv</span></span> continues to =
perform with session limits based on your device capabilities (number of co=
res/RAM).
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                                <hr>
                                             </section>
                                          </td>
                                       </tr>
                                    </tbody></table>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                =20
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">The default performance =
tier is FTDv50 when deploying a new <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">F=
TDv</span></span> device, or when provisioning the <span class=3D"ph"><span=
 class=3D"ph">FTDv</span></span> using the REST API.
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                =20
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph"><span=
 class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Base</span></span></spa=
n></span> licenses are subscription-based and mapped to performance tiers. =
Your virtual account needs to have the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph=
"><span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Base</span></span></span></span> li=
cense entitlements for the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FTDv</span=
></span> devices, as well as for <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph"><spa=
n class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Threat</span></span></span></span>, <span=
 class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Malw=
are</span></span></span></span>, and <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">=
<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">URL
                                                   												Filtering</s=
pan></span></span></span> licenses.
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                =20
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Each HA peer consumes on=
e entitlement, and the entitlements on each HA peer must match, including <=
span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">=
Base</span></span></span></span> license.
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                =20
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">A change in performance =
tier for an HA pair should be applied to the primary peer.</p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Universal PLR licensing =
is applied to each device in an HA pair separately. The secondary device wi=
ll not automatically mirror
                                       the performance tier of the primary =
device. It must be updated manually.
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                =20
                              </ul>
                             =20
                           </section>
                          =20
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic concept nested1" aria-labelledby=
=3D"ariaid-title62" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_49477">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title62">=
<span class=3D"ph">License Classic Devices (ASA FirePOWER and NGIPSv)</span=
></h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                        <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph">NGIPSv</span> dev=
ices and <span class=3D"ph">ASA FirePOWER</span> modules require Classic li=
censes. These devices are frequently referred to in this documentation as C=
lassic devices.
                        </p>
                        <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"olh_n=
ote" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                           <tbody><tr>
                              <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=3D"h=
eading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/us/td=
/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Important</b></p>
                              </td>
                              <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                 <section class=3D"note__content">
                                    <hr>If you are running Firepower hardwa=
re but not Firepower software, see licensing information for the software p=
roduct you are
                                    using. This documentation is not applic=
able.
                                    <hr>
                                 </section>
                              </td>
                           </tr>
                        </tbody></table></div>
                        <p class=3D"p">Classic licenses require a product a=
uthorization key (PAK) to activate and are device-specific. Classic licensi=
ng is sometimes
                           also referred to as "traditional licensing."=20
                        </p>
                     </section>

                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title63" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_49478">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title6=
3">Product License Registration Portal</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <p class=3D"p">When you purchase one or more Cla=
ssic licenses for Firepower features, you manage them in the Cisco Product =
License Registration
                              Portal:
                           </p>
                           <p class=3D"p"><a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https:/=
/cisco.com/go/license" target=3D"_blank">https://cisco.com/go/license</a></=
p>
                           <p class=3D"p">For more information on using thi=
s portal, see:</p>
                           <p class=3D"p"><a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https:/=
/slexui.cloudapps.cisco.com/SWIFT/LicensingUI/Quickstart" target=3D"_blank"=
>https://slexui.cloudapps.cisco.com/SWIFT/LicensingUI/Quickstart</a></p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">You will need your account creden=
tials in order to access these links.</p>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title64" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"concept_667E39369A974393AD5E6899=
D343DF93">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title6=
4">Service Subscriptions for Firepower Features (Classic Licensing)</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <p class=3D"p">Some features require a service s=
ubscription.</p>
                           <p class=3D"p">A service subscription enables a =
specific Firepower feature on a managed device for a set length of time. Se=
rvice subscriptions
                              can be purchased in one-, three-, or five-yea=
r terms. If a subscription expires, Cisco notifies you that you must renew =
the
                              subscription. If a subscription expires for a=
 Classic device, you might not be able to use the related features, dependi=
ng
                              on the feature type.
                           </p>
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table width=3D"10=
0%" border=3D"1" class=3D"table" id=3D"concept_667E39369A974393AD5E6899D343=

667E39369A974393AD5E6899D343DF93__table_6DF3CE6AC2884E248ECA255C656135FE__e=
ntry__2 ">

 TA is already present)</p>

                                 </tr>

                           <p class=3D"p">Your purchase of a managed device=
 that uses Classic licenses automatically includes Control and Protection l=
icenses. These
                              licenses are perpetual, but you must also pur=
chase a TA service subscription to enable system updates. Service subscript=
ions
                              for additional features are optional.=20
                           </p>

                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title6=
5">Classic License
                           	 Types and Restrictions
                        </h3>
                        <section class=3D"body refbody">
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"ID-2240-0000003=
5__section_E79AF7FA70E4449CB7C46F1AA4CD2C9B">
                              		=09
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-00000035__ID-224=
0-00000046">This section describes the types of Classic licenses available =
in a Firepower System deployment. The licenses you can enable
                                 on a device depend on its model, version, =
and the other licenses enabled.=20
                              </p>
                              		=09
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-00000035__ID-224=
0-00000048"> Licenses are model-specific for <span class=3D"ph">NGIPSv</spa=
n> devices and for <span class=3D"ph">ASA FirePOWER</span> modules. You can=
not enable a license on a managed device unless the license exactly matches=
 the device=E2=80=99s model.=20
                              </p>
                              		=09
                              		=09
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-00000035__ID-224=
0-00000032">There are a
                                 				few ways you may lose access to licens=
ed features in the Firepower System:=20
                              </p>
                              		=09
                              <ul class=3D"ul">
                                 <li class=3D"li" id=3D"ID-2240-00000035__l=
i_968760A839D14AF88C37E93068532A90">
                                    				=09
                                    <p class=3D"p"> You can remove Classic =
licenses from the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Managemen=
t Center</span></span>, which affects all of its managed devices.=20
                                    </p>
                                    			=09
                                 </li>
                                 <li class=3D"li" id=3D"ID-2240-00000035__l=
i_FDFD74EA0C484AE3827A084C36C06446">
                                    				=09
                                    <p class=3D"p"> You can disable license=
d
                                       						capabilities on specific manag=
ed devices.=20
                                    </p>
                                    			=09
                                 </li>
                              </ul>
                              		=09
                              <p class=3D"p"> Though there are some
                                 				exceptions, you cannot use the feature=
s associated with an expired or deleted
                                 				license.=20
                              </p>
                              		=09

0-00000051">The following table summarizes Classic licenses in the Firepowe=
r System. </p>

                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title66" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"ID-2240-000000e3">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le66">Protection
                              	 Licenses
                           </h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"ID-2240-0000=
00e3__section_6813A7FB1A7140E5A6BE9BBD8B3966D7">=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-000000e3__ID-=
2240-000000f8">A Protection license allows you to perform intrusion detecti=
on
                                    		  and prevention, file control, and S=
ecurity Intelligence filtering:=20
                                    	=09
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"ID-2240-000000e3=
__li_E7FF3C179336445FA5D4D8F52FE52304">=20
                                       			=20
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-000000e=
3__ID-2240-000000fa"><em class=3D"ph i" id=3D"ID-2240-000000e3__ID-2240-000=
000fc">Intrusion detection and prevention</em> allows you to analyze
                                          				network traffic for intrusion=
s and exploits and, optionally, drop offending
                                          				packets.=20
                                          			=20
                                       </p>=20
                                       		 =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"ID-2240-000000e3=
__li_DB7D24190B3F45B89A1D221FBD79DC3B">=20
                                       			=20
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-000000e=
3__ID-2240-000000fd"><em class=3D"ph i" id=3D"ID-2240-000000e3__ID-2240-000=
000ff">File control</em> allows you to detect and, optionally, block users =
from uploading (sending) or downloading (receiving) files of specific types
                                          over specific application protoco=
ls. <em class=3D"ph i" id=3D"ID-2240-000000e3__ID-2240-00000100"><span clas=
s=3D"ph">AMP for Networks</span></em>, which requires a Malware license, al=
lows you to inspect and block a restricted set of those file types based on=
 their dispositions.
                                         =20
                                       </p>=20
                                       		 =20
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"ID-2240-000000e3=
__li_A4BFF1E86902453EB201CB1E653B8DCD">=20
                                       			=20
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-000000e=
3__ID-2240-00000103"><em class=3D"ph i" id=3D"ID-2240-000000e3__ID-2240-000=
00105">Security Intelligence filtering</em> allows you to block =E2=80=94de=
ny traffic to and from=E2=80=94specific IP addresses, URLs, and DNS domain =
names, before the traffic is subjected
                                          to analysis by access control rul=
es. Dynamic feeds allow you to immediately block connections based on the l=
atest intelligence.
                                          Optionally, you can use a =E2=80=
=9Cmonitor-only=E2=80=9D setting for Security Intelligence filtering.=20
                                       </p>=20
                                       		 =20
                                    </li>
                                 </ul>
                                 		=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">A Protection license (along=
 with a
                                    				Control license) is automatically i=
ncluded in the purchase of any Classic managed
                                    				device. This license is perpetual, =
but you must also purchase a TA subscription to
                                    				enable system updates.=20
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">Although you can
                                    		  configure an access control policy =
to perform Protection-related inspection
                                    		  without a license, you cannot deplo=
y the policy until you first add a
                                    		  Protection license to the=20
                                    		  <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"p=
h">Firepower Management Center</span></span>,
                                    		  then enable it on the devices targe=
ted by the policy.=20
                                    	=09
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-000000e3__ID-=
2240-0000010a">If you delete your Protection license from the=20
                                    		  <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"p=
h">Firepower Management Center</span></span>
                                    		  or disable Protection on managed de=
vices, the=20
                                    		  <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"p=
h">Firepower Management Center</span></span>
                                    		  stops acknowledging intrusion and f=
ile events from the affected devices. As a
                                    		  consequence, correlation rules that=
 use those events as a trigger criteria stop
                                    		  firing. Additionally, the=20
                                    		  <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"p=
h">Firepower Management Center</span></span>
                                    		  will not contact the internet for e=
ither Cisco-provided or third-party Security
                                    		  Intelligence information. You canno=
t re-deploy existing policies until you
                                    		  re-enable Protection.=20
                                    	=09
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">Because a Protection
                                    		  license is required for URL Filteri=
ng, Malware, and Control licenses, deleting
                                    		  or disabling a Protection license h=
as the same effect as deleting or disabling
                                    		  your URL Filtering, Malware, or Con=
trol license.=20
                                    	=09
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title67" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"ID-2240-0000011b">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le67">Control
                              	 Licenses
                           </h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"ID-2240-0000=
011b__section_0D167970397B4B6FA55B4280A22F81A2">=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-0000011b__ID-=
2240-0000012e">A Control license allows you to implement user and applicati=
on control by adding user and application conditions to access
                                    control rules. To enable a Control lice=
nse on a managed device, you must also enable a Protection license. A Contr=
ol license
                                    is automatically included (along with a=
 Protection license) in the purchase of any Classic managed device. This li=
cense is
                                    perpetual, but you must also purchase a=
 TA subscription to enable system updates.=20
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">If you do not enable a Cont=
rol license for a Classic managed device, you can add user and application =
conditions to rules
                                    in an access control policy, but you ca=
nnot deploy the policy to the device.=20
                                 </p>=20
                                 		=20
                                 		=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-0000011b__ID-=
2240-00000142">If you delete a Control license from the <span class=3D"ph">=
<span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> or disable Con=
trol on individual devices:  =20
                                 </p>
                                 		=09
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">You can continue to e=
dit and delete existing configurations, but you cannot deploy those changes=
 to the affected devices.</p>
                                       			=09
                                    </li>
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">You cannot re-deploy =
existing access control policies if they include rules with user or applica=
tion conditions.</p>
                                       			=09
                                    </li>
                                 </ul>=20
                                 	=20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title68" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"ID-2240-00000147">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le68"> URL Filtering
                              	 Licenses for Classic Devices
                           </h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"ID-2240-0000=
0147__section_94660A4F86DF429297F4AE620ACFBDCF">=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-00000147__ID-=
2240-0000015a">URL filtering allows
                                    				you to write access control rules t=
hat determine the traffic that can traverse your
                                    				network based on URLs requested by =
monitored hosts, correlated with information
                                    				about those URLs. To enable a URL F=
iltering license, you must also enable a
                                    				Protection license. You can purchas=
e a URL Filtering license for Classic devices as
                                    				a services subscription combined wi=
th Threat &amp; Apps (TAC) or Threat &amp; Apps
                                    				and Malware (TAMC) subscriptions, o=
r as an add-on subscription (URL) for a system
                                    				where Threat &amp; Apps (TA) is alr=
eady enabled.=20
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=
=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                    <tbody><tr>
                                       <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" =
role=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam=
/en/us/td/i/templates/tip.gif"><br><p><b>Tip</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                          <section class=3D"note__content">
                                             <hr>=20
                                             		 =20
                                             <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-0=
0000147__ID-2240-0000015d">Without a URL Filtering license, you can specify=
 individual URLs
                                                			 or groups of URLs to al=
low or block. This gives you granular, custom control
                                                			 over web traffic, but d=
oes not allow you to use URL category and reputation
                                                			 data to filter network =
traffic.=20
                                                		 =20
                                             </p>=20
                                             	=09
                                             <hr>
                                          </section>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                 </tbody></table></div>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-00000147__ID-=
2240-00000160">Although you can add category and reputation-based URL
                                    		  conditions to access control rules =
without a URL Filtering license, the=20
                                    		  <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"p=
h">Firepower Management Center</span></span>
                                    		  will not download URL information. =
You cannot deploy the access control policy
                                    		  until you first add a URL Filtering=
 license to the=20
                                    		  <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"p=
h">Firepower Management Center</span></span>,
                                    		  then enable it on the devices targe=
ted by the policy.=20
                                    	=09
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-00000147__ID-=
2240-00000166">You may lose access to URL filtering if you delete the licen=
se
                                    		  from the=20
                                    		  <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"p=
h">Firepower Management Center</span></span>
                                    		  or disable URL Filtering on managed=
 devices. Also, URL Filtering licenses may
                                    		  expire. If your license expires or =
if you delete or disable it, access control
                                    		  rules with URL conditions immediate=
ly stop filtering URLs, and your=20
                                    		  <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"p=
h">Firepower Management Center</span></span>
                                    		  can no longer download updates to U=
RL data. You cannot re-deploy existing
                                    		  access control policies if they inc=
lude rules with category and
                                    		  reputation-based URL conditions.=20
                                    	=09
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=20
                              </section>
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title69" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"ID-2240-0000016b">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le69"> Malware Licenses
                              	 for Classic Devices
                           </h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"ID-2240-0000=
016b__section_DFDE67C704604FE49A1BF0D7C46753CF">=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">A Malware license allows yo=
u to perform Cisco Advanced Malware Protection (AMP) with <span class=3D"ph=
">AMP for Networks</span> and <span class=3D"ph">Cisco Threat Grid</span>. =
You can use managed devices to detect and block malware in files transmitte=
d over your network. To enable a Malware license,
                                    you must also enable Protection. You ca=
n purchase a Malware license as a subscription combined with Threat &amp; A=
pps (TAM) or
                                    Threat &amp; Apps and URL Filtering (TA=
MC) subscriptions, or as an add-on subscription (AMP) for a system where Th=
reat &amp; Apps
                                    (TA) is already enabled.=20
                                 </p>=20
                                 		=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-0000016b__ID-=
2240-0000018a">You configure <span class=3D"ph">AMP for Networks</span> as =
part of a file policy, which you then associate with one or more access con=
trol rules. File policies can detect your users
                                    uploading or downloading files of speci=
fic types over specific application protocols. <span class=3D"ph">AMP for N=
etworks</span> allows you to use local malware analysis and file preclassif=
ication to inspect a restricted set of those file types for malware.
                                    You can also download and submit specif=
ic file types to the <span class=3D"ph">Cisco Threat Grid</span> cloud for =
dynamic and Spero analysis to determine whether they contain malware. For t=
hese files, you can view the network
                                    file trajectory, which details the path=
 the file has taken through your network. The Malware license also allows y=
ou to add
                                    specific files to a file list and enabl=
e the file list within a file policy, allowing those files to be automatica=
lly allowed
                                    or blocked on detection.=20
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-0000016b__ID-=
2240-0000018f">Before you can deploy an access control policy that includes=
 <span class=3D"ph">AMP for Networks</span> configurations, you <strong cla=
ss=3D"ph b" id=3D"ID-2240-0000016b__ID-2240-00000194">must</strong> add a M=
alware license, then enable it on the devices targeted by the policy. If yo=
u later disable the license on the devices,
                                    you cannot re-deploy the existing acces=
s control policy to those devices.=20
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-0000016b__ID-=
2240-00000196">If you delete all your Malware licenses or they all expire, =
the system stops querying the AMP cloud, and also stops acknowledging
                                    retrospective events sent from the AMP =
cloud. You cannot re-deploy existing access control policies if they includ=
e <span class=3D"ph">AMP for Networks</span> configurations. Note that for =
a very brief time after a Malware license expires or is deleted, the system=
 can use existing
                                    cached file dispositions. After the tim=
e window expires, the system assigns a disposition of <code class=3D"ph cod=
eph" id=3D"ID-2240-0000016b__ID-2240-0000019c">Unavailable</code> to those =
files.=20
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-0000016b__ID-=
2240-0000019d">A Malware license is required only if you deploy <span class=
=3D"ph">AMP for Networks</span> and <span class=3D"ph">Cisco Threat Grid</s=
pan>. Without a Malware license, the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">=
Firepower Management Center</span></span> can receive AMP for Endpoints mal=
ware events and indications of compromise (IOC) from the AMP cloud.=20
                                 </p>
                                 		=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">See also important informat=
ion at <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/secu=
rity/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/file_policies_a=
nd_advanced_malware_protection.html#id_101648">License Requirements for Fil=
e and Malware Policies</a>.
                                 </p>=20
                                 	=20
                              </section>
                           </section>

></nav>

 aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title70" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"ID-2240-000002b0">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title7=
0">View Your Classic Licenses</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h4>
                           </section>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"st=
epTable" border=3D"0">
                              <tbody>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"ID-2240-000002=
b0__step_C1A423B176D2442E81D08AA0EE5449BA">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Do one of the fo=
llowing, depending on your needs:</p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                          				=09
                                          <div class=3D"tableContainer"><ta=
ble width=3D"100%" border=3D"1" class=3D"table frame-all">
                                             <caption></caption>
                                             <colgroup>
                                                <col style=3D"width:50%">
                                                <col style=3D"width:50%">
                                             </colgroup>
                                             <thead class=3D"thead">

n class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>; for example, 66:0=

                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Copy the license
                                          			 text from either the License =
Registration Portal display, or the email the
                                          			 License Registration Portal s=
ends you.=20
                                          		 =20
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                          				=09
                                          <div class=3D"tableContainer"><ta=
ble class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                             <tbody><tr>
                                                <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"t=
d_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                   <p><b>Important</b></p>&=
nbsp;
                                                </td>
                                                <td border=3D"0" class=3D"t=
d_faq">
                                                   <section class=3D"note__=
content">
                                                      					=09
                                                      <p class=3D"p">The li=
censing text block in the portal or email message may include more than one=
 license. Each license is bounded by a BEGIN
                                                         LICENSE line and a=
n END LICENSE line. Make sure that you copy and paste only one license at a=
 time.=20
                                                      </p>
                                                      				=09
                                                   </section>
                                                </td>
                                             </tr>
                                          </tbody></table></div>
                                          			=09
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"ID-2240-000002=
d9__step_2576EC3660554DB598841445F61DF0BF">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;7</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Return to the=20
                                          			 <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">=
Add Feature License</span> page in the=20
                                          			 <span class=3D"ph"><span clas=
s=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>=E2=80=99s
                                          			 web interface.
                                          		 =20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"ID-2240-000002=
d9__step_8D8CCDCAF64A41B9A11ECAC61E2D3D37">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;8</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Paste the licens=
e text into the=20
                                          			 <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" =
id=3D"ID-2240-000002d9__ID-2240-00000314">License</span> field.=20
                                          		 =20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"ID-2240-000002=
d9__step_AE2ADC0F5E21461FA4AE5D24630E5884">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;9</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click=20
                                          			 <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">=
Verify License</span>.=20
                                          		 =20
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">=
=20
                                          			=20
                                          <p class=3D"p">If the license is =
invalid, make sure that you correctly copied the
                                             				license text.=20
                                             			=20
                                          </p>=20
                                          		 =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"ID-2240-000002=
d9__step_D10985842A964F7F8D3E5E7A9D68D805">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;10</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click=20
                                          			 <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" =
id=3D"ID-2240-000002d9__ID-2240-00000316">Submit License</span>.=20
                                          		 =20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <section class=3D"section postreq" id=3D"ID-2240=
-000002d9__postreq_E907C26FC0344E378DEB4A4C5D740308">

itle tasklabel cB_Bold">What to do next</h4>

i_0F4D06189B3F4CE1B00FCE970D7C7EFA">=20
