                  <article class=3D"topic task nested1 no_summary_steps" ar=
ia-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title73" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_79783">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title73">=
How to Convert a Classic License for Use on an FTD Device</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                        <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"id_79783__=
d262094e9496">
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">You can convert licenses using ei=
ther the License Registration Portal (LRP) or the Cisco Smart Software Mana=
ger (CSSM), and
                              you can convert an unused Product Authorizati=
on Key (PAK) or a Classic license that has already been assigned to a devic=
e.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"ol=
h_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                              <tbody><tr>
                                 <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=
=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/=
us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Important</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                    <section class=3D"note__content">
                                       <hr>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">You cannot undo this =
process.  You cannot convert a Smart License to a Classic license, even if =
the license was originally
                                          a Classic license.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <hr>
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody></table></div>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">In documentation on Cisco.com, Cl=
assic licenses may also be referred to as "traditional" licenses. </p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                        <section class=3D"section prereq p" id=3D"id_79783_=
_d262094e9453">
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h3 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">Before you begin</h3>
                           </section>
                          =20
                           <ul class=3D"ul">
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">It is easiest to convert a =
Classic license to a Smart License when it is still an unused PAK that has =
not yet been assigned
                                    to a product instance.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Your hardware must be able =
to run <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span=
></span>. See the <cite class=3D"cite"><em class=3D"ph i">Cisco Firepower C=
ompatibility Guide</em></cite> at <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cis=
co.com/c/en/us/support/security/defense-center/products-device-support-tabl=
es-list.html" target=3D"_blank">https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/secur=
ity/defense-center/products-device-support-tables-list.html</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">You must have a Smart Accou=
nt.  If you do not have one, create one.  See <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"htt=
ps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guid=
e/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_81767">Creat=
e a Smart Account to Hold Your Licenses</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">The PAKs or licenses that y=
ou want to convert must appear in your Smart Account. </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">If you convert using the Li=
cense Registration Portal instead of the Cisco Smart Software Manager, you =
must have your Smart
                                    Account credentials in order to initiat=
e the conversion process.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                           </ul>
                          =20
                        </section>
                        <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                           <h3 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitle t=
asklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h3>
                        </section>
                        <hr noshade=3D"">
                        <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"stepT=
able" border=3D"0">
                           <tbody>
                              <tr class=3D"li step">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">The conversion proc=
ess you will follow depends on whether or not the license has been consumed=
:</p>
                                    <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                      =20
                                       <ul class=3D"ul">
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">If the PAK that=
 you want to convert has never been used, follow instructions for convertin=
g a PAK.</p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">If the PAK you =
want to convert has already been assigned to a device, follow instructions =
for converting a Classic license.
                                               =20
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">Make sure your =
existing classic license is still registered to your device.</p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                       </ul>
                                      =20
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">See instructions fo=
r your type of conversion (PAK or installed Classic license) in the followi=
ng documentation: </p>
                                    <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                      =20
                                       <ul class=3D"ul">
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">To convert PAKs=
 or licenses using the LRP: </p>
                                            =20
                                             <ul class=3D"ul">
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">To view a=
 video that steps you through the License Registration Portal part of the c=
onversion process, click <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://salesconnect.cis=
co.com/#/content-detail/7da52358-0fc1-4d85-8920-14a1b7721780" target=3D"_bl=
ank">https://salesconnect.cisco.com/#/content-detail/7da52358-0fc1-4d85-892=
0-14a1b7721780</a>.
                                                   </p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Search fo=
r "Convert" in the following document: <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://ci=
sco.app.box.com/s/mds3ab3fctk6pzonq5meukvcpjizt7wu" target=3D"_blank">https=
://cisco.app.box.com/s/mds3ab3fctk6pzonq5meukvcpjizt7wu</a>.=20
                                                   </p>
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">There are=
 three conversion procedures.  Choose the conversion procedure applicable t=
o your situation.</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Sign in t=
o the License Registration Portal (LRP) at <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https:=
//tools.cisco.com/SWIFT/LicensingUI/Home" target=3D"_blank">https://tools.c=
isco.com/SWIFT/LicensingUI/Home</a> and follow the instructions in the docu=
mentation above.
                                                   </p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                             </ul>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">To convert PAKs=
 or licenses using CSSM: </p>
                                            =20
                                             <ul class=3D"ul">
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p"><cite cla=
ss=3D"cite"><em class=3D"ph i">Converting Hybrid Licenses to Smart Software=
 Licenses QRG</em></cite>:
                                                   </p>
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p"><a class=
=3D"xref" href=3D"https://community.cisco.com/t5/licensing-enterprise-agree=
ments/converting-hybrid-licenses-to-smart-software-licenses-qrg/ta-p/362860=
9?attachment-id=3D134907" target=3D"_blank">https://community.cisco.com/t5/=
licensing-enterprise-agreements/converting-hybrid-licenses-to-smart-softwar=
e-licenses-qrg/ta-p/3628609?attachment-id=3D134907</a></p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Sign in t=
o CSSM at <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://software.cisco.com/#SmartLicens=
ing-LicenseConversion" target=3D"_blank">https://software.cisco.com/#SmartL=
icensing-LicenseConversion</a> and follow the instructions for your type of=
 conversion (PAK or installed Classic license) in the documentation above.
                                                   </p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                             </ul>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                       </ul>
                                      =20
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">Freshly install <sp=
an class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> o=
n your hardware.
                                    </p>
                                    <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">See the instructions =
for your hardware at <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/u=
s/support/security/firepower-ngfw/products-installation-guides-list.html" t=
arget=3D"_blank">https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/security/firepower-n=
gfw/products-installation-guides-list.html</a>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">If you will use <sp=
an class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Device
                                             											Manager</span></spa=
n> to manage this device as a standalone device:
                                    </p>
                                    <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">See information about=
 licensing the device in the <em class=3D"ph i"><cite class=3D"cite">Cisco =
Firepower Threat Defense Configuration Guide for Firepower Device Manager</=
cite></em>  at <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/supp=
ort/security/firepower-ngfw/products-installation-and-configuration-guides-=
list.html" target=3D"_blank">https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/security=
/firepower-ngfw/products-installation-and-configuration-guides-list.html</a=
>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Skip the rest of this=
 procedure.</p>
                                      =20
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;5</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">If you have already=
 deployed Smart Licensing on your <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fir=
epower Management Center</span></span>:=20
                                    </p>
                                    <ol type=3D"a" class=3D"ol substeps">
                                       <li class=3D"li substep substepexpan=
d">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Set up Smart =
Licensing on your new <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threa=
t Defense</span></span> device.
                                          </p>
                                          <section class=3D"itemgroup info"=
>
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D=
"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/=
configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.ht=
ml#id_75162">Assign Licenses to Multiple Managed Devices</a>.
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                          </section>
                                       </li>
                                       <li class=3D"li substep substepexpan=
d">
                                          <p class=3D"ph cmd">Verify that t=
he new Smart License has been successfully applied to the device.</p>
                                          <section class=3D"itemgroup info"=
>
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D=
"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/=
configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.ht=
ml#task_E06E766894744E2B81D476F727569502">View FTD Licenses and License Sta=
tus</a>.
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                          </section>
                                       </li>
                                    </ol>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;6</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">If you have not yet=
 deployed Smart Licensing on your <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fir=
epower Management Center</span></span>:=20
                                    </p>
                                    <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                      =20
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xref"=
 href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/config=
uration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_=
75733">How to License Firepower Threat Defense Devices</a>. (Skip any steps=
 that do not apply or that you have already completed.)
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody>
                        </table></div>
                        <hr noshade=3D"">
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></nav=
>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic task nested1 no_summary_steps" ar=
ia-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title74" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"ID-2240-00000342">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title74">=
Assign Licenses to Managed Devices from the Device Management Page</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                        <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"ID-2240-00=
000342__context_B19658E5777F44D9A824E418E51C54E6">=20
                           	=09
                           <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2240-00000342__ID-2240-0=
000035a">Although there are some exceptions, you cannot use the features as=
sociated with a license if you disable it on a managed device.</p>
                           		=09
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"ol=
h_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                              <tbody><tr>
                                 <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=
=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/=
us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                    <section class=3D"note__content">
                                       <hr>
                                       			=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">For container instanc=
es on the same <span class=3D"ph">security module/engine</span>, you apply =
the license to each instance; note that the <span class=3D"ph">security mod=
ule/engine</span> consumes only one license per feature for all instances o=
n the <span class=3D"ph">security module/engine</span>.
                                       </p>
                                       		=09
                                       <hr>
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody></table></div>
                           		=09

 apply the licenses to the cluster as a whole; note that each unit in the c=

                     <nav class=3D"faq_minitoc">
                        <ul class=3D"ulchildlink">
                           <li><a href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/=

ing_the_firepower_system.html#id_50660__section_fkj_2rr_rz">License Expirat=
ion vs. Service Subscription Expiration</a></li>
                        </ul>
                        <ul class=3D"ulchildlink">
                           <li><a href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/=
docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licens=
ing_the_firepower_system.html#id_50660__section_tf3_pcl_rz">Smart Licensing=
</a></li>
                        </ul>
                        <ul class=3D"ulchildlink">
                           <li><a href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/=
docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licens=
ing_the_firepower_system.html#id_50660__d262094e10088">Specific License Res=
ervation</a></li>
                        </ul>
                        <ul class=3D"ulchildlink">
                           <li><a href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/=
docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licens=
ing_the_firepower_system.html#id_50660__d262094e10126">Classic Licensing</a=
></li>
                        </ul>
                        <ul class=3D"ulchildlink">
                           <li><a href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/=
docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licens=
ing_the_firepower_system.html#id_50660__section_u2w_ztq_rz">Subscription Re=
newals</a></li>
                        </ul>
                     </nav>
                     <section class=3D"body refbody">
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_50660__section_=
fkj_2rr_rz">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">License Expirat=
ion vs. Service Subscription Expiration</h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"dl=
">
                              <tbody>
                                 <tr class=3D"dt table_faq">
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                       <p><b>Q.</b>&nbsp;
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">Do feature license=
s expire?</td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"dd table_faq">
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                       <p><b>A.</b>&nbsp;
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Strictly speaking, fe=
ature licenses do not expire. Instead, the service subscriptions that suppo=
rt those licenses expire.
                                          <span class=3D"ph">For details ab=
out service subscriptions, see "Service Subscriptions for Firepower Feature=
s" in the <em class=3D"ph i"><cite class=3D"cite">Firepower Management Cent=
er Configuration Guide</cite></em> available from <a class=3D"xref" href=3D=
"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/security/defense-center/products-ins=
tallation-and-configuration-guides-list.html" target=3D"_blank">https://www=
.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/security/defense-center/products-installation-an=
d-configuration-guides-list.html</a>.</span></p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>
                          =20
                        </section>
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_50660__section_=
tf3_pcl_rz">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Smart Licensing=
</h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"dl=
">
                              <tbody>
                                 <tr class=3D"dt table_faq">
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                       <p><b>Q.</b>&nbsp;
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">Can a Product Inst=
ance Registration Token expire?</td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"dd table_faq">
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                       <p><b>A.</b>&nbsp;
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">A token can expire if=
 it is not used to register a product within the specified validity period.=
 You set the number of days
                                          that the token is valid when you =
create the token in the Cisco Smart Software Manager. If the token expires =
before you use
                                          it to register a <span class=3D"p=
h"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>, you must create a new token.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">After you use the tok=
en to register a <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>, t=
he token expiration date is no longer relevant. When the token expiration d=
ate elapses, there is no impact on the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph=
">FMC</span></span> that you used the token to register.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Token expiration date=
s do not affect subscription expiration dates.</p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">For more information,=
 see the <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/web/fw/softwarewor=
kspace/smartlicensing/SSMCompiledHelps/" target=3D"_blank"><em class=3D"ph =
i">Cisco Smart Software Manager User Guide</em></a>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"dt table_faq">
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                       <p><b>Q.</b>&nbsp;
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">How can I tell if =
my Smart Licenses/service subscriptions are expired or about to expire?</td=
>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"dd table_faq">
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                       <p><b>A.</b>&nbsp;
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">To determine when a s=
ervice subscription will expire (or when it expired), review your entitleme=
nts in the <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://software.cisco.com/#module/Sma=
rtLicensing" target=3D"_blank">Cisco Smart Software Manager</a>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">On the <span class=3D=
"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>, you can determine whether a serv=
ice subscription for a feature license is currently in compliance by choosi=
ng <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Syste=
m</span><span class=3D"ph"> (<a href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/t=
d/i/400001-500000/450001-460000/451001-452000/451292.jpg" class=3D"show-ima=
ge-alone" title=3D"system gear icon"><img class=3D"image" src=3D"https://ww=
w.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/450001-460000/451001-452000/4512=
92.jpg" alt=3D"system gear icon"></a>)</span></span><span class=3D"ph menuc=
ascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol"></span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontr=
ol">Licenses</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Smart Licenses</span>=
</span></span>. On this page, a table summarizes the Smart License entitlem=
ents associated with this <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span><=
/span> via its product registration token. You can determine whether the se=
rvice subscription for the license is currently in compliance
                                          based on the <span class=3D"ph ui=
control">License Status</span> field.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">On <span class=3D"ph"=
><span class=3D"ph">FDM</span></span>, use the Smart License page to view t=
he current license status for the system: Click <span class=3D"ph uicontrol=
">Device</span>, then click <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">View Configuration=
</span> in the Smart License summary.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">In addition, the Cisc=
o Smart Software Manager will send you a notification 3 months before a lic=
ense expires. </p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"dt table_faq">
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                       <p><b>Q.</b>&nbsp;
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">What happens if my=
 Smart License/subscription expires?</td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"dd table_faq">
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                       <p><b>A.</b>&nbsp;
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">If a purchased servic=
e subscription expires, you can see in <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph=
">FMC</span></span> and in your Smart Account that your account is out of c=
ompliance. Cisco notifies you that you must renew the subscription;
                                          see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"htt=
ps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guid=
e/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_50660__subsc=
ription_renewals">Subscription Renewals</a>. There is no other impact.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>
                          =20
                        </section>
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_50660__d262094e=
10088">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Specific Licens=
e Reservation</h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                          =20
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"dl=
">
                              <tbody>
                                 <tr class=3D"dt table_faq">
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                       <p><b>Q.</b>&nbsp;
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">What happens if my=
 Specific License Reservation expires?</td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"dd table_faq">
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                       <p><b>A.</b>&nbsp;
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">SLR licenses are term=
-based. </p>
                                      =20
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">If required licenses =
are unavailable or expired, the following actions are restricted:</p>
                                      =20
                                       <ul class=3D"ul">
                                         =20
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">Device registra=
tion</p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                         =20
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">Policy deployme=
nt</p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                         =20
                                       </ul>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>
                          =20
                        </section>
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_50660__d262094e=
10126">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Classic Licensi=
ng</h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"dl=
">
                              <tbody>
                                 <tr class=3D"dt table_faq">
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                       <p><b>Q.</b>&nbsp;
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">How can I tell if =
my Classic licenses/service subscriptions are expired or about to expire?</=
td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"dd table_faq">
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                       <p><b>A.</b>&nbsp;
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">On the <span class=3D=
"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>, choose <span class=3D"ph"><span =
class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span><span class=3D"ph"> =
(<a href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/450001-460=
000/451001-452000/451292.jpg" class=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"system ge=
ar icon"><img class=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i=
/400001-500000/450001-460000/451001-452000/451292.jpg" alt=3D"system gear i=
con"></a>)</span></span><span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph ui=
control"></span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Licenses</span> &gt; <sp=
an class=3D"ph uicontrol">Classic Licenses</span></span></span>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">On this page, a table=
 summarizes the Classic licenses you have added to this <span class=3D"ph">=
<span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">You can determine whe=
ther the service subscription for the license is currently in compliance ba=
sed on the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Status</span> field.=20
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">You can determine whe=
n the service subscription will expire (or when it expired) by the date in =
the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Expires</span> field.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">You can also obtain t=
his information by reviewing your license information in the <a class=3D"xr=
ef" href=3D"http://www.cisco.com/web/go/license" target=3D"_blank">Cisco Pr=
oduct License Registration Portal</a>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"dt table_faq">
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                       <p><b>Q.</b>&nbsp;
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">What does this mea=
n: 'IPS Term Subscription is still required for IPS'?</td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"dd table_faq">
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                       <p><b>A.</b>&nbsp;
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">This message merel=
y informs you that Protect and Control functionality requires not only a ri=
ght-to-use license (which never
                                       expires), but also one or more assoc=
iated service subscriptions, which must be renewed periodically. If the ser=
vice subscriptions
                                       you want to use are current and will=
 not expire soon, no action is required.=20
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"dt table_faq">
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                       <p><b>Q.</b>&nbsp;
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">What happens if my=
 Classic license/subscription expires?</td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"dd table_faq">
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                       <p><b>A.</b>&nbsp;
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"td_faq">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">If a service subscrip=
tion supporting a Classic license expires, Cisco notifies you that you must=
 renew the subscription; see
                                          <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https:/=
/www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fp=
mc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_50660__subscript=
ion_renewals">Subscription Renewals</a>.=20
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">You might not be able=
 to use the related features, depending on the feature type:</p>
                                      =20
                                       <table width=3D"100%" border=3D"1" c=
lass=3D"table frame-all" id=3D"id_50660__table_ttf_1zq_rz">
                                          <caption><span class=3D"table--ti=
tle-label tabletitle">Table 7. </span><span class=3D"tabletitle">Expiration=
 Impact for Classic Licenses/Subscriptions</span></caption>
                                          <colgroup>
                                             <col style=3D"width:18.1818181=
81818183%">
                                             <col style=3D"width:27.2727272=
7272727%">
                                             <col style=3D"width:54.5454545=
4545454%">
                                          </colgroup>
                                          <thead class=3D"thead">
                                             <tr>
                                                <th font-weight=3D"bold" cl=
ass=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" id=3D"id_50660__table_ttf_1zq_rz__entry__1"=
>
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Classic L=
icense</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </th>
                                                <th font-weight=3D"bold" cl=
ass=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" id=3D"id_50660__table_ttf_1zq_rz__entry__2"=
>
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Possible =
Supporting Subscriptions</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </th>
                                                <th font-weight=3D"bold" cl=
ass=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" id=3D"id_50660__table_ttf_1zq_rz__entry__3"=
>
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Expiratio=
n Impact</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </th>
                                             </tr>
                                          </thead>
                                          <tbody class=3D"tbody">
                                             <tr>
                                                <td class=3D"entry colsep-1=
 rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_50660__table_ttf_1zq_rz__entry__1 ">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Control</=
p>
                                                  =20
                                                </td>
                                                <td class=3D"entry colsep-1=
 rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_50660__table_ttf_1zq_rz__entry__2 ">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">TA, TAC, =
TAM, TAMC</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </td>
                                                <td class=3D"entry colsep-1=
 rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_50660__table_ttf_1zq_rz__entry__3 ">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">You can c=
ontinue to use existing  functionality, but you cannot download VDB updates=
, including application signature updates.</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </td>
                                             </tr>
                                             <tr>
                                                <td class=3D"entry colsep-1=
 rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_50660__table_ttf_1zq_rz__entry__1 ">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Protectio=
n</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </td>
                                                <td class=3D"entry colsep-1=
 rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_50660__table_ttf_1zq_rz__entry__2 ">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">TA, TAC, =
TAM, TAMC</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </td>
                                                <td class=3D"entry colsep-1=
 rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_50660__table_ttf_1zq_rz__entry__3 ">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">You can c=
ontinue to perform intrusion inspection, but you cannot download intrusion =
rule updates.</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </td>
                                             </tr>
                                             <tr>
                                                <td class=3D"entry colsep-1=
 rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_50660__table_ttf_1zq_rz__entry__1 ">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">URL Filte=
ring</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </td>
                                                <td class=3D"entry colsep-1=
 rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_50660__table_ttf_1zq_rz__entry__2 ">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">URL, TAC,=
 TAMC </p>
                                                  =20
                                                </td>
                                                <td class=3D"entry colsep-1=
 rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_50660__table_ttf_1zq_rz__entry__3 ">
                                                  =20
                                                   <ul class=3D"ul" id=3D"i=
d_50660__ul_o4n_szq_rz">
                                                      <li class=3D"li">
                                                        =20
                                                         <p class=3D"p">Acc=
ess control rules with URL conditions immediately stop filtering URLs. </p>
                                                        =20
                                                      </li>
                                                      <li class=3D"li">
                                                        =20
                                                         <p class=3D"p">Oth=
er policies (such as SSL policies) that filter traffic based on URL categor=
y and reputation immediately stop doing so.</p>
                                                        =20
                                                      </li>
                                                      <li class=3D"li">
                                                        =20
                                                         <p class=3D"p">The=
 <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> can no longer down=
load updates to URL data.
                                                         </p>
                                                        =20
                                                      </li>
                                                      <li class=3D"li">
                                                        =20
                                                         <p class=3D"p">You=
 cannot re-deploy existing policies that perform URL category and reputatio=
n filtering.</p>
                                                        =20
                                                      </li>
                                                   </ul>
                                                  =20
                                                </td>
                                             </tr>
                                             <tr>
                                                <td class=3D"entry colsep-1=
 rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_50660__table_ttf_1zq_rz__entry__1 ">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Malware</=
p>
                                                  =20
                                                </td>
                                                <td class=3D"entry colsep-1=
 rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_50660__table_ttf_1zq_rz__entry__2 ">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p"><span cla=
ss=3D"ph">
                                                         										<span cl=
ass=3D"ph">AMP</span></span>, TAM, TAMC=20
                                                   </p>
                                                  =20
                                                </td>
                                                <td class=3D"entry colsep-1=
 rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_50660__table_ttf_1zq_rz__entry__3 ">
                                                  =20
                                                   <ul class=3D"ul" id=3D"i=
d_50660__ul_z34_b1r_rz">
                                                      <li class=3D"li">
                                                        =20
                                                         <p class=3D"p">For=
 a very brief time, the system can use existing cached file dispositions. A=
fter the time window expires, the system assigns
                                                            a disposition o=
f <code class=3D"ph codeph">Unavailable</code> to those files.
                                                         </p>
                                                        =20
                                                      </li>
                                                      <li class=3D"li">
                                                        =20
                                                         <p class=3D"p">The=
 system stops querying the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">AMP
                                                                  									=
		Cloud</span></span>, and stops acknowledging retrospective events sent fr=
om the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">AMP
                                                                  									=
		Cloud</span></span></p>
                                                        =20
                                                      </li>
                                                      <li class=3D"li">
                                                        =20
                                                         <p class=3D"p">You=
 cannot re-deploy existing access control policies if they include <span cl=
ass=3D"ph">
                                                               										<s=
pan class=3D"ph">AMP</span></span> for <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph=
">FTD</span></span> configurations.
                                                         </p>
                                                        =20
                                                      </li>
                                                   </ul>
                                                  =20
                                                </td>
                                             </tr>
                                          </tbody>
                                       </table>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>
                          =20
                        </section>

                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title77">=
Additional Information about Firepower Licensing</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body refbody">
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_64141__d262094e=
10713">

                           <p class=3D"p">For additional information to hel=
p resolve common licensing questions, see the following documents:</p>
                          =20

equently Asked Questions (FAQ) about Firepower Licensing</cite> document at=
:
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p"><a class=3D"xref" href=3D"h=
ttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/licensing/faq/firep=
ower-license-FAQ.html" target=3D"_blank">https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/d=

ttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/roadmap/firepower-l=
icenseroadmap.html" target=3D"_blank">https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs=

                  <article class=3D"topic concept nested1" aria-labelledby=
=3D"ariaid-title78" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_60544">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title78">=
Cisco Success Network</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_60544__d262094e=
10770">
                           		=09
                           <p class=3D"p">Cisco Success Network is a user-e=
nabled cloud service. When you enable Cisco Success Network, a secure conne=
ction is established
                              between the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D=
"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> and the Cisco cloud to strea=
m usage information and statistics. Streaming telemetry provides a mechanis=
m to select data of
                              interest from the Firepower System and to tra=
nsmit it in a structured format to remote management stations for the follo=
wing
                              benefits:
                           </p>
                           		=09
                           <ul class=3D"ul">
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">To inform you of available =
unused features that can improve the effectiveness of the product in your n=
etwork.</p>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">To inform you of additional=
 technical support services and monitoring that might be available for your=
 product. </p>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                              			=09
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">(If you integrate with <spa=
n class=3D"ph">SecureX</span>) To summarize appliance and device status in =
<span class=3D"ph">SecureX</span> tiles. This lets you see at a glance, for=
 example, whether all of your
                                    						devices are running optimal softw=
are versions.
                                 </p>
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">For more information about =
<span class=3D"ph">SecureX</span>, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://ww=
w.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-=
config-guide-v70/analyze_events_using_external_tools.html#Cisco_Concept.dit=
a_46512a06-f8c2-4dce-a09f-1f46b6e87f55">Integrate with Cisco SecureX</a>.
                                 </p>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">To help Cisco improve our p=
roducts.</p>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                           </ul>
                           		=09
                           		=09
                           		=09
                           <p class=3D"p">The Firepower Management Center e=
stablishes and maintains the secure connection between the Firepower Manage=
ment Center and
                              the Cisco cloud at all times, after you have =
enabled either Cisco Support Diagnostics or Cisco Success Network. You can =
turn
                              off this connection at any time by disabling =
both Cisco Success Network and Cisco Support Diagnostics, which disconnects=
 <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></=
span> from the Cisco cloud. However, when Cisco Support Diagnostics is enab=
led, a secure connection is established and maintained
                              between the Firepower Threat Defense and the =
Cisco cloud along with the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower =
Management Center</span></span> and Cisco cloud. Therefore, when the Cisco =
Support Diagnostics is disabled, both these secure connections are turned o=
ff.
                           </p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_60544__d262094e=
10829">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Enabling Cisco =
Success Network</h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">You enable Cisco Success Network =
when you register the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Manag=
ement Center</span></span> with the Cisco Smart Software Manager. See <a cl=
ass=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepow=
er/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_sys=
tem.html#task_E14666F0D32E45FE820B52C9D3103B6F">Register Smart Licenses</a>=
.
                           </p>
                           		=09
                           <p class=3D"p">You can view your current Cisco S=
uccess Network enrollment status on the <span class=3D"ph menucascade"><spa=
n class=3D"ph uicontrol">Licences</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">=
Smart Licenses</span></span> page, and you can change your enrollment statu=
s. See <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/secu=
rity/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_f=
irepower_system.html#id_65602">Changing Cisco Success Network Enrollment</a=
>.
                           </p>
                           		=09
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"ol=
h_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                              <tbody><tr>
                                 <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=
=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/=
us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                    <section class=3D"note__content">
                                       <hr>
                                       			=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">The Cisco Success Net=
work feature is disabled if the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firep=
ower Management Center</span></span> has a valid <span class=3D"ph">Smart S=
oftware Manager
                                             										On-Prem</span> (form=
erly known as Smart Software Satellite Server) configuration, or uses Speci=
fic License Reservation.
                                       </p>
                                       		=09
                                       <hr>
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody></table></div>
                          =20
                        </section>
                     </section>

                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links">
                        <ul class=3D"ullinks">

                           <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https:=
//www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/f=
pmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_65602">Changing=
 Cisco Success Network Enrollment</a></li>
                        </ul>
                     </nav>

                     <article class=3D"topic reference nested2" aria-labell=
edby=3D"ariaid-title79" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_76820">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title7=
9">Cisco Success Network Telemetry Data</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body refbody">
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_76820__d2620=
94e10912">
                              		=09
                              <p class=3D"p">Cisco Success Network allows e=
nrolled <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</=
span></span>s to continuously stream real time configuration and operating =
state information to the Cisco Success Network cloud. Collected
                                 and monitored data include the following:=
=20
                              </p>
                              		=09
                              <ul class=3D"ul">
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                    				=09
                                    <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b">E=
nrolled device information</strong>=E2=80=94This includes the <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> device=
 name, model, serial number, UUID, system uptime, and Smart Licensing infor=
mation; see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs=
/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_=
the_firepower_system.html#id_85550">Enrolled Device Data</a>.=20
                                    </p>
                                    			=09
                                 </li>
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                    				=09
                                    <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b">S=
oftware information</strong>=E2=80=94This includes software information abo=
ut the enrolled <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management =
Center</span></span>, such as version number, rule update version, geolocat=
ion database version, and vulnerability database (VDB) version information;
                                       see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https:=
//www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/f=
pmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_85556">Software=
 Version Data</a>.
                                    </p>
                                    			=09
                                 </li>
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                    				=09
                                    <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b">M=
anaged device information</strong>=E2=80=94This includes information about =
all the managed devices associated with the enrolled <span class=3D"ph"><sp=
an class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>, including device=
 names, device models, serial numbers, software versions, and licenses in u=
se per device; see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/=
td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/lic=
ensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_85559">Managed Device Data</a>.
                                    </p>
                                    			=09
                                 </li>
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                    				=09
                                    <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b">D=
eployment information</strong>=E2=80=94This includes information about poli=
cy deploymnents. After you configure your deployment, and any time you chan=
ge that configuration,
                                       you must deploy the changes to affec=
ted devices; see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td=
/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licen=
sing_the_firepower_system.html#id_85571">Deployment Information</a>.=20
                                    </p>
                                    			=09
                                 </li>
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                    				=09
                                    <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b">F=
eature usage</strong>=E2=80=94This includes feature-specific policy and lic=
ensing information:
                                    </p>
                                    				=09
                                    <ul class=3D"ul">
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                          						=09
                                          <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"p=
h b">URL filtering</strong>=E2=80=94This includes how many URL filtering li=
censes are configured and deployed to devices, and how many devices have po=
licies
                                             deployed that are using the UR=
L filtering capability.
                                          </p>
                                          					=09
                                       </li>
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                          						=09
                                          <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"p=
h b">Intrusion prevention</strong>=E2=80=94This includes how many managed d=
evices are configured for intrusion prevention,and whether a device has bee=
n enabled for
                                             Threat Intelligence Director (=
TID).
                                          </p>
                                          					=09
                                       </li>
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                          						=09
                                          <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"p=
h b">Malware detection</strong>=E2=80=94 This includes how many malware lic=
enses are configured and deployed to devices, and how many devices have pol=
icies deployed
                                             that are using the malware det=
ection capability.=20
                                          </p>
                                          					=09
                                       </li>
                                    </ul>
                                    			=09
                                 </li>
                              </ul>
                              	=09
                           </section>
                        </section>
