                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title84" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_109246">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le84">TLS/SSL Inspection Event Data</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_109246__d=
262094e11819">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">By default, the Firepower S=
ystem cannot inspect traffic encrypted with the Secure Socket Layer (SSL) p=
rotocol or its successor,
                                    the Transport Layer Security (TLS) prot=
ocol. <em class=3D"ph i">TLS/SSL inspection</em> enables you to either bloc=
k encrypted traffic without inspecting it, or inspect encrypted or decrypte=
d traffic with access
                                    control. The following tables describe =
statistics.shared with Cisco Success Network about encrypted traffic.=20
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_109246__d=
262094e11827">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Handshake=
 Process </h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">When the system detects a T=
LS/SSL handshake over a TCP connection, it determines whether it can decryp=
t the detected traffic.
                                    As the system handles encrypted session=
s, it logs details about the traffic.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table width=
=3D"100%" border=3D"1" class=3D"table frame-all">
                                    <caption><span class=3D"table--title-la=
bel tabletitle">Table 12. </span><span class=3D"tabletitle">TLS/SSL Inspect=
ion - Handshake Telemetry Data</span></caption>
                                    <colgroup>
                                       <col style=3D"width:50%">
                                       <col style=3D"width:50%">
                                    </colgroup>
                                    <thead class=3D"thead">
                                       <tr>
                                          <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D=
"entry" id=3D"id_109246__entry__1">Data Point </th>
                                          <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D=
"entry" id=3D"id_109246__entry__2">Example Value</th>
                                       </tr>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody class=3D"tbody">
                                       <tr>
                                          <td class=3D"entry" headers=3D"id=
_109246__entry__1 ">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">The system repo=
rts the following applied actions when the traffic <strong class=3D"ph b">c=
annot be decrypted</strong> and is:=20
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                             <ul class=3D"ul">
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Blocked</=
p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Blocked w=
ith a TCP reset </p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Not decry=
pted</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                             </ul>
                                            =20
                                          </td>
                                          <td class=3D"entry valign-middle"=
 headers=3D"id_109246__entry__2 ">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">An integer valu=
e of 0 or greater</p>
                                            =20
                                          </td>
                                       </tr>
                                       <tr>
                                          <td class=3D"entry" headers=3D"id=
_109246__entry__1 ">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">The system repo=
rts the following applied actions when the traffic <strong class=3D"ph b">c=
an be decrypted</strong>: =20
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                             <ul class=3D"ul">
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">With a kn=
own private key</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">With a re=
placement key only</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">By resign=
ing a self-signed certificate</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">By resign=
ing the server certificate</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                             </ul>
                                            =20
                                          </td>
                                          <td class=3D"entry valign-middle"=
 headers=3D"id_109246__entry__2 ">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">An integer valu=
e of 0 or greater</p>
                                            =20
                                          </td>
                                       </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                 </table></div>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_109246__d=
262094e11916">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Cache Dat=
a</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">After a TLS/SSL handshake c=
ompletes, the managed device caches encrypted session data, which allows se=
ssion resumption without
                                    requiring the full handshake. The manag=
ed device also caches server certificate data, which allows faster handshak=
e processing
                                    in subsequent sessions.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table width=
=3D"100%" border=3D"1" class=3D"table frame-all">
                                    <caption><span class=3D"table--title-la=
bel tabletitle">Table 13. </span><span class=3D"tabletitle">TLS/SSL Inspect=
ion -  Cache Telemetry Data</span></caption>
                                    <colgroup>
                                       <col style=3D"width:50%">
                                       <col style=3D"width:50%">
                                    </colgroup>
                                    <thead class=3D"thead">
                                       <tr>
                                          <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D=
"entry" id=3D"id_109246__entry__7">Data Point </th>
                                          <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D=
"entry" id=3D"id_109246__entry__8">Example Value</th>
                                       </tr>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody class=3D"tbody">
                                       <tr>
                                          <td class=3D"entry" headers=3D"id=
_109246__entry__7 ">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">The system cach=
es encrypted session data and server certificate data, and reports on the <=
strong class=3D"ph b">cache</strong> per SSL connections, specifically:
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                             <ul class=3D"ul">
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">The numbe=
r of times SSL session information was cached</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">The numbe=
r of times the SSL certificate validation cache was hit</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">The numbe=
r of times the SSL certificate validation cache lookup missed </p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">The numbe=
r of times the SSL original certificate cache was hit</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">The numbe=
r of times the SSL original certificate cache lookup missed</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">The numbe=
r of times the SSL resigned certificate cache was hit</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">The numbe=
r of times the SSL resigned certificate cache lookup missed </p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                             </ul>
                                            =20
                                          </td>
                                          <td class=3D"entry valign-middle"=
 headers=3D"id_109246__entry__8 ">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">An integer valu=
e of 0 or greater</p>
                                            =20
                                          </td>
                                       </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                 </table></div>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_109246__d=
262094e11989">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Certifica=
te Status</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">The system evaluates encryp=
ted traffic and reports the certificate status of the encrypting server.</p=
>
                                =20
                                 <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table width=
=3D"100%" border=3D"1" class=3D"table frame-all">
                                    <caption><span class=3D"table--title-la=
bel tabletitle">Table 14. </span><span class=3D"tabletitle">TLS/SSL Inspect=
ion -  Certificate Status Telemetry Data</span></caption>
                                    <colgroup>
                                       <col style=3D"width:50%">
                                       <col style=3D"width:50%">
                                    </colgroup>
                                    <thead class=3D"thead">
                                       <tr>
                                          <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D=
"entry" id=3D"id_109246__entry__11">Data Point </th>
                                          <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D=
"entry" id=3D"id_109246__entry__12">Example Value</th>
                                       </tr>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody class=3D"tbody">
                                       <tr>
                                          <td class=3D"entry" headers=3D"id=
_109246__entry__11 ">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">The system eval=
uates encrypted traffic based on the <strong class=3D"ph b">certificate sta=
tus</strong> of the encrypting server, and reports the number of connection=
s where the SSL Certificate:
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                             <ul class=3D"ul">
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Is valid<=
/p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Is expire=
d</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Has an in=
valid issuer</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Has an in=
valid signature</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Is not ch=
ecked </p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Is not ye=
t valid</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Is revoke=
d</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Is self s=
igned </p>
                                                  =20

n</p>

e of 0 or greater</p>

                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_109246__d=
262094e12072">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Failure R=
eason</h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">The system evaluates encryp=
ted traffic and reports the failure reason when the system fails to decrypt=
 traffic.</p>
                                =20
                                 <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table width=
=3D"100%" border=3D"1" class=3D"table frame-all">
                                    <caption><span class=3D"table--title-la=
bel tabletitle">Table 15. </span><span class=3D"tabletitle">TLS/SSL Inspect=
ion -  Failure Telemetry Data</span></caption>
                                    <colgroup>
                                       <col style=3D"width:50%">
                                       <col style=3D"width:50%">
                                    </colgroup>
                                    <thead class=3D"thead">
                                       <tr>
                                          <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D=
"entry" id=3D"id_109246__entry__15">Data Point </th>
                                          <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D=
"entry" id=3D"id_109246__entry__16">Example Value</th>
                                       </tr>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody class=3D"tbody">
                                       <tr>
                                          <td class=3D"entry" headers=3D"id=
_109246__entry__15 ">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">The system eval=
uates encrypted traffic and reports the <strong class=3D"ph b">failure reas=
on</strong> when the system fails to decrypt traffic due to:
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                             <ul class=3D"ul">
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">A decrypt=
ion error</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Making a =
policy verdict during the handshake</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Making a =
policy verdict before the handshake</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Compressi=
on being negotiated</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">An uncach=
ed session</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">An interf=
ace in passive mode</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">An unknow=
n cipher suite</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">An unsupp=
orted cipher suite</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                             </ul>
                                            =20
                                          </td>
                                          <td class=3D"entry valign-middle"=
 headers=3D"id_109246__entry__16 ">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">An integer valu=
e of 0 or greater</p>
                                            =20
                                          </td>
                                       </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                 </table></div>
                                =20
                              </section>
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_109246__d=
262094e12150">
                                 <h5 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Version</=
h5>
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">The system evaluates encryp=
ted traffic and reports the negotiated TLS/SSL version per connection. </p>
                                =20
                                 <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table width=
=3D"100%" border=3D"1" class=3D"table frame-all">
                                    <caption><span class=3D"table--title-la=
bel tabletitle">Table 16. </span><span class=3D"tabletitle">TLS/SSL Inspect=
ion -  Version Telemetry Data</span></caption>
                                    <colgroup>
                                       <col style=3D"width:50%">
                                       <col style=3D"width:50%">
                                    </colgroup>
                                    <thead class=3D"thead">
                                       <tr>
                                          <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D=
"entry" id=3D"id_109246__entry__19">Data Point </th>
                                          <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D=
"entry" id=3D"id_109246__entry__20">Example Value</th>
                                       </tr>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody class=3D"tbody">
                                       <tr>
                                          <td class=3D"entry" headers=3D"id=
_109246__entry__19 ">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">The system eval=
uates encrypted traffic and reports the negotiated <strong class=3D"ph b">v=
ersion</strong> per SSL connections where:
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                             <ul class=3D"ul">
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">SSLv2 was=
 negotiated </p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">SSLv3 was=
 negotiated</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">An unknow=
n version was negotiated</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">TLSv1.0 w=
as negotiated</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">TLSv1.1 w=
as negotiated</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">TLSv1.2 w=
as negotiated</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                  =20
                                                   <p class=3D"p">TLSv1.3 w=
as negotiated</p>
                                                  =20
                                                </li>
                                             </ul>
                                            =20
                                          </td>
                                          <td class=3D"entry valign-middle"=
 headers=3D"id_109246__entry__20 ">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">An integer valu=
e of 0 or greater</p>
                                            =20
                                          </td>
                                       </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                 </table></div>
                                =20
                              </section>
                           </section>

></nav>

                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic reference nested3" aria-lab=
elledby=3D"ariaid-title85" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_109252">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le85">Snort Restart Data</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body refbody">
                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_109252__d=
262094e12260">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">When the traffic inspection=
 engine referred to as the Snort process on a managed device restarts, insp=
ection is interrupted
                                    until the process resumes. Creating or =
deleting a user-defined application, or activating or deactivating a system=
 or custom
                                    application detector immediately restar=
ts the Snort process without going through the deploy process. The system w=
arns you
                                    that continuing restarts the Snort proc=
ess and allows you to cancel; the restart occurs on any managed device in t=
he current
                                    domain or in any of its child domains.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table width=
=3D"100%" border=3D"1" class=3D"table frame-all">
                                    <caption><span class=3D"table--title-la=
bel tabletitle">Table 17. </span><span class=3D"tabletitle">Snort Restart T=
elemetry Data</span></caption>

                                       <col style=3D"width:50%">
                                    </colgroup>

"entry" id=3D"id_109252__entry__1">Data Point </th>

"entry" id=3D"id_109252__entry__2">Example Value</th>
                                       </tr>

_109252__entry__1 ">

restarts when you enable or disable a custom application detector</p>
                                            =20
                                          </td>
                                          <td class=3D"entry" headers=3D"id=
_109252__entry__2 ">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">An integer valu=
e of 0 or greater</p>
                                            =20
                                          </td>
                                       </tr>
                                       <tr>
                                          <td class=3D"entry" headers=3D"id=
_109252__entry__1 ">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">Count of snort =
restarts when you create or modify a custom application detector</p>
                                            =20
                                          </td>
                                          <td class=3D"entry" headers=3D"id=
_109252__entry__2 ">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">An integer valu=
e of 0 or greater</p>
                                            =20
                                          </td>
                                       </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                 </table></div>
                                =20
                              </section>

le86">Contextual Cross-Launch Data</h4>

                              <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_109465__d=
262094e12338">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">The contextual cross-launch=
 feature allows you to quickly find more information about potential threat=
s in web-based resources
                                    outside of the Firepower Management Cen=
ter. You can click directly from an event in the event viewer or dashboard =
in the FMC
                                    to the relevant information in an exter=
nal resource. This lets you quickly gather context around a specific event =
based on
                                    its IP addresses, ports, protocol, doma=
in, and/or SHA 256 hash.=20
                                 </p>

=3D"100%" border=3D"1" class=3D"table frame-all">

                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title8=
8">Changing Cisco Success Network Enrollment</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                           <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"id_6560=
2__d262094e12496">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">You enable Cisco Success Netwo=
rk when you register the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Ma=
nagement Center</span></span> with the Cisco Smart Software Manager. After =
that, use the following procedure to view or change enrollment status.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D=
"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                 <tbody><tr>
                                    <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" rol=
e=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en=
/us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                       <section class=3D"note__content">
                                          <hr>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Cisco Success Netw=
ork does not work in evaluation mode.</p>
                                         =20

                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody></table></div>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">

e tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h4>

epTable" border=3D"0">

r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <span clas=
s=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span> &gt; <span =
class=3D"ph uicontrol">Licenses</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Sm=
art Licenses</span></span>.=20

                                    </td>
                                 </tr>

r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

nse Status, next to Cisco Success Network, click <span class=3D"ph uicontro=
l">Enabled/Disabled</span> control for the Cisco Success Network feature to=

r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

                                    </td>

r=3D"0">

tion provided by Cisco, choose whether you want to <span class=3D"ph uicont=
rol">Enable Cisco Success Network</span>, and click <span class=3D"ph uicon=
trol">Apply Changes</span>.

iguration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/system_configuration.html#id_61646">(=

                  <article class=3D"topic concept nested1" aria-labelledby=
=3D"ariaid-title89" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_112854">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title89">=
Cisco Support Diagnostics</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_112854__d262094=
e12586">
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Cisco Support Diagnostics is a us=
er-enabled cloud-based TAC support service. When enabled, a secure connecti=
on is established
                              between the Firepower Management Center (FMC)=
, and Firepower Threat Defense (FTD) on one side and the Cisco cloud on the=
 other
                              side, to stream system health related informa=
tion.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Cisco Support Diagnostics provide=
s an enhanced user experience during troubleshooting by allowing Cisco TAC =
to securely collect
                              essential data from your device during a TAC =
case. Moreover, operational health data is periodically collected and proce=
ssed
                              through Cisco's automated problem detection s=
ystem to proactively notify you of any issues. While the data collection se=
rvice
                              during a TAC case is available for all users =
with support contracts, the proactive notification service is only availabl=
e
                              to users with specific service contracts.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">The Firepower Management Center e=
stablishes and maintains the secure connection between the Firepower Manage=
ment Center and
                              the Cisco cloud at all times, after you have =
enabled either Cisco Support Diagnostics or Cisco Success Network. You can =
turn
                              off this connection at any time by disabling =
both Cisco Success Network and Cisco Support Diagnostics, which disconnects=
 these
                              features from the Cisco cloud. However, when =
Cisco Support Diagnostics is enabled, a secure connection is established an=
d
                              maintained between the FTD and the Cisco clou=
d along with the FMC and Cisco cloud. Therefore, when the Cisco Support Dia=
gnostics
                              is disabled both these secure connections are=
 turned off.
                           </p>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Administrators can view a sample =
data set which is collected from the FMC by following the steps in <a class=
=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/=
70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/troubleshooting_the_system.htm=
l#id_15121">Producing Troubleshooting Files for Specific System Functions</=
a> to generate a troubleshooting file, and then by opening the file to view=
 it.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">The FMC sends the collected data =
to the regional cloud specified on the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System<=
/span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Integration</span> &gt; <span clas=
s=3D"ph uicontrol">Cloud Services</span> page. Note that this setting is al=
so used for Cisco Support Network, described at <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"h=
ttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/gu=
ide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#id_60544">Cis=
co Success Network</a>, and the Cisco Threat Response integration described=
 at <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/securit=
y/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/analyze_events_usi=
ng_external_tools.html#id_102554">Event Analysis with Cisco SecureX threat =
response</a>.
                           </p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_112854__d262094=
e12624">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Enabling Cisco =
Support Diagnostics</h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">You enable Cisco Support Diagnost=
ics when you register the Firepower Management
                              Center with the Cisco Smart Software Manager.=
 See <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/securi=
ty/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_fir=
epower_system.html#task_E14666F0D32E45FE820B52C9D3103B6F">Register Smart Li=
censes</a>.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">You can view your current Cisco S=
upport Diagnostics enrollment status on the <span class=3D"ph menucascade">=
<span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Licenses</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontr=
ol">Smart Licenses</span></span> page, and you can change your enrollment s=
tatus. See<a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/s=
ecurity/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_th=
e_firepower_system.html#id_112867">Changing Cisco Support Diagnostics Enrol=
lment</a>.
                           </p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                     </section>

g Cisco Support Diagnostics Enrollment</a></li>
                        </ul>
                     </nav>

.
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">

                                          <div class=3D"tableContainer"><ta=
ble class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                             <tbody><tr>
                                                <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"t=
d_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                   <p><b>Note</b></p>&nbsp;
                                                </td>
                                                <td border=3D"0" class=3D"t=
d_faq">

content">
                                                     =20

he information provided next to the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Enabled/Di=
sabled</span> control before you proceed.
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                   </section>
                                                </td>
                                             </tr>

                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>

                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                    </td>

r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <span clas=
s=3D"ph uicontrol">Apply Changes</span>.

                           </table></div>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <section class=3D"section postreq" id=3D"id_1128=
67__d262094e12734">
                              <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                 <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiont=
itle tasklabel cB_Bold">What to do next</h4>
                              </section>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">If you have enabled Cisco Supp=
ort Diagnostics, verify the regional cloud setting at <span class=3D"ph men=
ucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph=
 uicontrol">Integration</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol"> Cloud Ser=
vices</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Cisco Cloud Region</span></s=
pan> to establish where the system data is sent.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                        </section>

nav>

                                          supported on all FMCs and FTD dev=
ices. Previously,
                                          support was limited to FMCs, Fire=
power 4100/9300
                                          with FTD, and FTDv for Azure.
                                       </p>

FMC, FTD</p>

                                 </tr>
                                =20

                                   =20
                                    <td class=3D"entry align-left colsep-1 =
rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_83700__ID-2170-00000ecf ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Cisco Support Diagnos=
tics</p>
                                      =20
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                   =20
                                    <td class=3D"entry align-left colsep-1 =
rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_83700__ID-2170-00000ed1 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">6.5</p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                   =20
                                    <td class=3D"entry align-left colsep-1 =
rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_83700__ID-2170-00000ed3 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p"><em class=3D"ph i">Ci=
sco Support Diagnostics</em> (sometimes
                                          called <em class=3D"ph i">Cisco P=
roactive Support</em>) sends
                                          configuration and operational hea=
lth data to
                                          Cisco, and processes that data th=
rough our
                                          automated problem detection syste=
m, allowing us to
                                          proactively notify you of issues.=
 This feature
                                          also allows Cisco TAC  to collect=
 essential
                                          information from your devices dur=
ing the course of
                                          a TAC case.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">During upgrades and r=
eimages, you may be asked
                                          to enroll. You can also change yo=
ur enrollment at
                                          any time. For details, see <a cla=
ss=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepowe=
r/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_syst=
em.html#id_112854">Cisco Support Diagnostics</a>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">In Version 6.5.0, Cis=
co Support Diagnostics
                                          support is limited to select
                                          platforms.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">New/Modified screens:=
 <span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span> =
&gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Licenses</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph ui=
control">Smart Licenses</span></span></p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Supported platforms: =
FMC, Firepower 4100/9300,
                                          FTDv for Azure
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                   =20
                                 </tr>
                                =20

rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_83700__ID-2170-00000ecf ">

s Network allows <span class=3D"ph">SecureX</span> to display appliance and=
 device status
                                          information

                                      =20
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                   =20
                                    <td class=3D"entry align-left colsep-1 =
rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_83700__ID-2170-00000ed1 ">

rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_83700__ID-2170-00000ed3 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">For general informati=
on about the <span class=3D"ph">SecureX</span> integration, see <a class=3D=
"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/=
configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/analyze_events_using_external_too=
ls.html#Cisco_Concept.dita_46512a06-f8c2-4dce-a09f-1f46b6e87f55">Integrate =
with Cisco SecureX</a> and

topic.=20

nstance capability for the

ower <span class=3D"ph">4100/</span>9300</span></p>

rowsep-1" headers=3D"id_83700__ID-2170-00000ed3 ">

ltiple <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span=
></span> container instances on a <span class=3D"ph">Firepower <span class=
=3D"ph">4100/</span>9300</span>. You only need a single license per feature=
 per
                                          security module/engine. The base =
license is
                                          automatically assigned to each in=
stance.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">New/Modified screens:=
 <span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span> =
&gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Licenses</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph ui=
control">Smart Licenses</span></span></p>

<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span=
> on the <span class=3D"ph">Firepower <span class=3D"ph">4100/</span>9300</=
span></p>

; }

t: 1em; left: -1em; padding-inline-start: var(--padding); position: absolut=
e; right: 0px; top: -0.5em; width: 1em; }

.checkbox::after { border: 1px solid white; border-radius: 2px; content: ""=
; height: 1em; left: var(--padding); position: absolute; top: var(--padding=
); width: 1em; }

-end-width: 0px; content: ""; height: 0.2em; left: calc(.3em + var(--paddin=
g)); opacity: 0; position: absolute; top: calc(.3em  + var(--padding)); tra=
nsform: rotate(-45deg); width: 0.5em; }

ow: hidden; }

; }

gle-gray-100); }

r, .slow-speed-option [type=3D"checkbox"]:checked + .slow-speed-toggle::bef=
ore { background: var(--google-blue-300); }
